text_review: my new dell eight thousand , two hundred desktop came pre-installed with xp and after using it for a half a month it has been very very stable and the look of the operating system is really great the os can be in your face at times but you can change the way everything looks and make many things nonexistent so you never see them the os starts really fast and i have not seen the dreaded blue screen at all also my application opening times have much faster than with windows ninety-eight or windows me.after getting the feel of the os i decided to upgrade my dell laptop which was running windows me the upgrade went very very smooth and i did not have any trouble during the install after having the new os on my laptop just for a few days i have not seen the constant windows me crash and my laptop starts faster my applications run quicker and my computer looks really cool with xp on it the only draw back that i have noticed with xp on my laptop is that it really uses a lot more memory usage than windows me if you have only 64mb on your laptop which is what i have i would suggest upgrading your memory before or after you upgrade in conclusion i would really suggest buying windows xp because it really is microsoft's best home version of windows yet and it is a really solid product

text_review: rhythm games are not my sort of thing that is why i found myself surprised to be enjoying this game so much the main advantage that this game has over its competitors is a good story with gameplay features borrowed from professor layton and extremely catchy beats i found myself humming the tunes from this fairly shortly after playing it for the first time.the plot of the game is focused around a young frenchman called raphael who goes around by night disguised as the notorious phantom r an art thief of great style and sophistication the police are baffled at the ability of this young redheaded thief in a fashionable suit and fedora to disappear undoubtedly they asked the random redheaded civilian with glasses and no hat for information but he did not see anything it is that kind of game raphael is searching for his father who went missing years before during his pursuit he finds himself entwined in the risen emperor napoleon's dastardly plans to take over the world fortunately his men are susceptible to timed dance moves.sound ridiculous good it is meant to the plot is one of the most entertaining things about this game amusing and insane it takes our heroes on a tour of paris and its environs and paris is very much on display here the city looks gorgeous even in the 2d that dominates the gameplay when you do get to see a cinematic cutscene in glorious 3d no less it really sours.the rhythm games are cleverly based around this plot for example when sneaking into the louvre you have to follow a beat to hide behind convenient statues and avoid the guards when fighting napoleon's men you have to punch them as they bounce at you in synchronized fashion when eluding policemen on roller skates you have to jump or duck to avoid capture and my personal favorite you get to defend yourself against your archrival's pi child charlie who attempts to apprehend you by kicking a flaming football at your face they are all fun not a little bit silly and have a catchy beat.the parts of the game not revolving around playing rhythm games owe a very large debt to professor layton not so much the puzzle aspect but the way that you move your character along a map and use the touchscreen to interact with the characters and scenery on it they even have playcoins you can collect by tapping random areas of the screen the character and street designs are very nice these are seen at their full effect when the cutscenes start these cutscenes are beautifully animated and really capture a spirit of adventure i wish they would make this into an anime so we could see it all animated the 3d is used to good effect in these especially the first cutscene which has raphael dancing around a room filled with chandeliers the rest of the game does not use it much and it is often easier to just turn it off.most of this game takes place on the bottom screen the top screen has a map and is used for all the wonderful 3d cutscenes but when traveling you pay attention to the touchscreen in battles the top screen becomes important these battles alternate between having you tap buttons on the bottom screen with your stylus and hitting buttons no you do not have to do both at the same time that would be horrifyingly difficult.the downsides to the game are fairly minor but annoying the rating system is messed up the game does not record your best scores only an average of all your scores this means that if you want the game to save you getting an a-rank score you have to get it right on your first time which is almost impossible another flaw is the grading system for these ranks it is too heavily focused on what your last move was you can get a perfect score right up until the end and then flub only the last note dropping you down to a c-rank it is very irritating.if any of this sounds compelling try the demo it is available for free on the nintendo store this is one fun game even for non rhythm game fans while the game does not always add up to the sum of its parts nevertheless it provides a fun ride.do store this is one fun game even for non rhythm game fans while the game does not always add up to the sum of its parts nevertheless it provides a fun ride

text_review: i have been using bitdefender for the past couple of years i found the two thousand and eight version for three computers for two years at a great price when it was running out i went looking for a similar deal and found one i noticed a couple of unpolished elements when installing there were a lot of dos command prompt windows opening in the background on the screen very briefly i did not have to interact with any of them and they went away almost immediately so there is no harm to it it is just a little unpolished i should also mention that the update for it is big it will ask to download the updated installer then after a few minutes when that is downloaded and run the updates for the program are currently over seventy-five mb i think that is probably the case with many anti-virus programs but just be aware if you are on dial-up you will be downloading for quite some time i uninstalled that old from a laptop and a desktop the desktop went fine but the laptop failed to uninstall i tried to get the uninstall program off bitdefender's website but the link they pointed to was dead eventually i found the cd and reinstalled which failed but the cd had the uninstaller which worked i only mention this because it is a little worrisome that if the last program had those issues that this version might when i eventually uninstall it i like this version of the program it has several different modes ranging from novice hides settings to expert showing all of it and is very easy to change between them my absolute favorite part though is the you are not fully protected system in past programs i have used if you disable some feature you constantly get the little alert icon that you are at risk bitdefender two thousand and ten lets you choose which of those things it monitors for so i did not want the anti-spam because i only use web mail so i told it not to bother me that i would deleted it it may be a small thing but to me it is a huge annoyance saver.so far i cannot tell if the scanner is faster or not it scans at only about a quarter of the number of files per second as the old program but it supposedly has an intelligent monitoring system which lets it avoid rescanning files that have not changed and thus could not have picked up an infection so while it was not that fast on the first scan in theory it will only get faster moving forward it intentionally skipped thousands of files.default is a daily scan which in my opinion is complete overkill unless you have a kid in your house if the resident protection is running all the time you can get by with once or twice a week thankfully the scheduling is very easy and you can even set the scans to take low priority which is a nice touch.in terms of detection bitdefender is not the highest rated scanner but it is far from the lowest it is an excellent budget anti-virus package and more than adequate for most people's needs considering how reasonable the pricing is i would happily recommend however since i have only used it a week or so if it does do anything really weird i will update my review to mention it.update 8/ 3/10- finally had to use my printer and guess what bitdefender has killed it i cannot use my network printer so i am dropping this review a couple stars i killed its firewall and turned the windows one on again guess what i can print again i wasted two hours dealing trying to fix it before i gave up unacceptable behavior in a firwall.ce saver so far i cannot tell if the scanner is faster or not it scans at only about a quarter of the number of text_review: my friend wanted a digital camera he was looking at still units but after he starting talking more about movies than stills i talked him into a video camera over a still camera this type of product has been out for awhile but most of them have been primitive needed tons of light and the videos were of generally low quality i have canon slr units their digital sensors are some of the best in my opinion so i started checking out this camera most consumer sites have glowing review after glowing review on the fs100 we have had this unit about three months we have used it quite a lot under mostly daylight conditions where these units most often fall down is in the amount of light they need to get good pictures my old tape camcorder can easily get good video in candle light this one is not quite that good but it is dang close most often with these units low light means unacceptably grainy images ... this unit does pretty well with that from what i have seen at least in middle quality mode the book states minimum light something like one hundred lux which is around dim room light after i got this i took it to the target parking lot at night and shot some video under just the parking lot mercury lamps ... i was looking for two things ... grainy images and color shifts caused by the non-daylight colored lamps in the parking area lighting i happened to catch a guy riding across the parking lot on his bike at a pretty good clip and tested the camera by tracking him across the lot and zooming in and out all the while ... the image was a bit grainy but it was acceptable and surprisingly good for a camera of this variety at night and under non daylight colored light ... i e canon's sensor is pretty darn good my first canon slr is pretty brain dead when it comes to mixed lighting situations but they seem to have straightened up their act in later products in that regard white balance logic there is a competing product of this type made by samsung the price isgenerally a bit lower than the canon i have looked at that unit but not had a chance to use one on that unit folks are saying the buttons are too flimsy another reason i went with this one we use this camera to shoot a lot of fast action sca heavy fighting i find that the default auto setting does not result in a fast enough shutter speed to catch very fast action this unit has a mode that allows you to choose the shutter speed while the camera chooses the aperature ... i fixed the blurred action by setting the camera shutter speed to 1/250 or faster and that has cured that issue completely i have not shot in full quality mode ... really do not need it ... middle quality mode is pretty darn good even displayed on a large flat panel although i am sure a true hd video snob would sniff indignantly at it this camera supports sdhd so you are not limited to two gig memory cards the sixteen gig cards are currently out like three hours in middle quality mode and thirty-two gig cards are also available but still too expensive if you get this camera i suggest you buy an image bank handheld self-powered device with notebook hard drive in it so you can clean off your cards and reuse them this camera does not have touch screen i really do not miss that at all the joystick is very serviceable i find the menus easy to navigate and the camera has a good variety of settings if i did not mention it before the camera can also take still images that are very acceptable overall what i think about it i like the camera i think if it was up to me i would redesign the zoom lever yes it is under your fingers as you hold the camera ... but i find it a little bit awkward especially when zooming in higher magnifications i would prefer to have the zoom on the back where i can hit it with my thumb canon does their usual thing of monopolizing batteries and accessories for this camera by not releasing tech specs so other companies can make products that work with it batteries are outrageous at eighty bucks plus each you can find them on amazon for around sixty but that is still outrageous in my book you can find knock off batteries on ebay that power the camera but they do not have the internal electronics and thus the camera cannot detect the charge and they will not charge on the camera one of your first purchases should be two sixteen gig sdhc cards they are not too high if you shop around four gig cards will suffice to start but get the biggest ones you can get and stick with a quality manufacturer as well i did not pick high speed cards for this camera i have not text_review: this cd was recommended to me on amazon because of my purchases of the locust the dillinger escape plan an albatross and daughters so i expected some really fast and intense music upon my first listen of pizza i was pretty disappointed it is not very fast aside from a few moments none of which are locust or dep-fast its poppy moments are completely pointless the drums sound quite dull the synth work is tacky and a lot of the screaming just sounds halfhearted i would not call it an emotional rollercoaster as another reviewer who happens to be in the band did i guess the synth is supposed to make them nintendocore but they really do not even achieve that very well it sounds a little like a video game but completely lacks any nintendo feeling i listened to it about a dozen more times and it began to grow on me i even found myself singing p i-z-z-a at one point around my friends its concise length probably helps fifty minutes of this would get old quick i never watched teenage mutant ninja turtles so i was not necessarily excited to hear the tnmt theme song at the end and having almost nothing to do with pizza i think the album would be stronger without it i just found it hard to get excited about this album it is a neat concept if you can call five songs that mention pizza a concept it is a little fun to tell people i am listening to horse the band but it will not even come close to touching your grindcore sweet tooth

text_review: i would have easily given this play food set five stars but for two details that bothered me with the wooden serving tray the first is that it is pictured both on amazon and on the box it came in as being solid wood it is not the bottom of the try is mdf that said it may be mdf created with e zero glues as i can detect absolutely no formaldehyde odor from it and i have a nose for vocs often much to my dismay the second detail is that there was a sharp shard of wood which had splintered up on the edge of the tray we glued it down with some elmer's time will tell if that holds it or if we will have to disfigure the tray by removing it and sanding it down however now that i have gotten those relatively minor gripes out of the way the rest of the set is pretty fantastic there are two main courses a veggie burger and a fish we are vegetarians so this is more food for the girls cats and bears and so forth which is something they really desired i might add both pieces cut into six and seven pieces respectively they are quite easy to cut and unlike many velcro-attached play foods the velcro is inlaid allowing the pieces to be flush with one another thus when the items are put together they look like whole solid pieces and do not just fall apart the veggie burger is finished with a durable chip-resistant matte paint stain and has grill imprints on one side the fish is unfinished wood and has grill imprints as well both are lovely the veggie burger can be adorned with a pat of butter the fish with a small slice of lemon these are not velcro attached the side dishes include four each of green beans fries and carrots these are are simple and easily-recognizable the fork and knife are natural wood with blue-stained handles and seem quite durable there is also an attractive thin cardboard insert with a lettuce bed and a few tomato slices which jazzes up the not-as-attractive-as-advertised mdf-bottomed serving tray sadly i am not convinced this piece will last very long as it is just too bendy but i suppose it would be easy enough to make your own variation to replace it the scale of the food is almost relative to our haba erzi and plan toys play food collection probably a wee bit larger but a wee bit smaller than something like melissa and doug nonetheless i could see it pleasing fans of both it does have the distinctive advantage over melissa and doug of no reeking of formaldehyde and other mystery chemicals and claims to have been processed in an ecologically sustainable and socially responsible manner bottom line no doubt i would buy this again save for the tray this set is beautifully crafted and very high quality it will last and last it is got a fantastic array of play stuff for an unusually fair price oh and my five-year old daughter played with it for two hours after it arrived today so it is got her seal of approval

text_review: cyril scott 1879-1970 had the misfortune of too easy success early in his career and mounting neglect for the rest of his life from as early as one thousand , nine hundred and thirty he was being written off as an imitator of debussy who had nothing more worth saying does this adventurous cd confirm or refute this view though a lifelong lover of his music i have to confess that the muses scott's first mature symphony is like the curate's egg good in parts but unacceptable as a whole it starts well with a sinister and brooding opening movement but the middle movements are underdeveloped and the choral finale is a watered down version of the general dance at the end of ravel's daphnis and chloe the second piano concerto of one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-eight is representative of the far more individual idiom that scott developed when he returned to composing in the late 1940s the harmony has an acrid complexity the phrases are brief and there is none of the effortless note-spinning that led colin matthews to dismiss his earlier music as vapid unfortunately the work never establishes a convincing relationship between the soloist and the orchestra and is full of striking gestures that lead nowhere the recently recorded second string quartet played by archaeus quartet on the dutton label is a far more attractive example of his late style that leaves neptune which is a revised version of disaster at sea a long tone poem depicting the sinking of the titanic that was written in the late 1910s there was a tardy first performance in one thousand , nine hundred and thirty-three when the critics panned the work as mere film music scott responded by removing the more crudely programmatic parts of the score in a revised and renamed version of the work which was published in one thousand , nine hundred and thirty-five but has gone unperformed till now i am happy to hail it as a masterpiece the tragic atmosphere is sustained throughout and the writing is beautifully diaphanous and full of highly original orchestral effects which evoke the surge and the spray and the careering bulk of the doomed ship with uncanny vividness there is nothing finer in scott than the bleak epilogue depicting the bare and icy ocean as night sets in in the wake of the famous film and with the original title restored could not this work achieve a belated popularity certainly this skilfully crafted and richly sonorous recording makes the strongest possible case it and the neapolitan rhapsody available on a marco polo cd seem to me the two strongest works by scott for orchestra alone

text_review: the d70 is the digital slr to record daily life and life events with a six megapixel resolution limits the size of prints you can make with it to about eleven by seventeen if this is not a problem for you then this is your digital camera if you want to be able to make larger prints with good resolution then you need to spend a great deal more money for a higher resolution digital camera about 5,000 or stick with film i keep my old n90 for these purposes the d70 comes bundled with the excellent and compact 18-70 nikkor lens and one en-el three battery to get started with the camera i suggest the following in addition one extra en-el three lithium-ion battery two 2gb 80x compactflash cards with write acceleration wa technology one cf card reader for your computer firewire or usb connection depending upon your needs as time and money permit you may want to add the following a telephoto lens for wildlife and sporting events the 70-300 mm f4 -5.6 g af nikkor is a great value and complements the bundled lens nicely if money is not an object step up to the 70-300 ed or the 70-200 f2 eight with vibration reduction a good macro lens such as the af micro nikkor 105mm f2 eight polarizing filters for both the kit lens and the telephoto get nikon filters there is no sense in spending money for nikkor lenses and then putting junk filters on them a bag to carry all this stuff this will get you nicely started further down the line you may wish to get the following a speedlight either the sb six hundred or eight hundred a tripod and ballhead be sure to check prices at b h photo as well as those shown here they have a tremendous selection and have long been known and trusted by serious photographers in addition i would suggest that anyone who buys a d70 join nikonians there or literally tens of thousands of people who are more than happy to help you with any question you may haveabout nikon cameras lenses and other equipment as well as help you with your text_review: this game is a far better experience than any cod experiences in the past years where their games have become stale run and shoot experiences the combination of killzones cover system and intelligent enemy ai conveys a sense of military realism and challenge enemy's flank use grenades to flush you out of cover while allowing the player to feel like every kill and battle won was earned through precise positioning and strategy all of which equates to an impressive experience of depth despite the shallow and often times stereotypical narrative speaking of immersion playing this game with the playstation move and sharp shooter is a surreal experience it takes getting use to at first and my suggestion is to practice this scheme in the bot zone which is an offline simulated multi player mode this both allows you to calibrate the move scheme to your liking and at the same time allows you to get acclimated to the pacing and class system of the online multi player which has become my new addiction on its own right after playing through the campaign with a dual shock and than sharp shooter i am now an online fiend in cod if your not up to par with getting a high kill death ratio you are seemingly made useless and target practice by helicopters attack dogs and whatever cod mechanism that unbalances the online experience for us non aiming experts in killzone the class base system allows me to contribute to my team without having to be a terminator in one game i had the highest score dispite having one of the worst kdr of my team i was an engineer and medic taking up points fixing weapons depots and setting up gun turrets which did some killing for me and as a medic getting points healing people left and right when the battles around me became intense which was the norm in ever online match each match was highly competitive and never once made me feel like i could not get involved even with getting slaughtered by a mech which is easy to take down as anengineer fixing the wasp turrets to insure those huge mechs do not become too over powering balanced that is what this entire game feels from the difficulty in the story mode which has challenging ai but gives you powerful guns that never allow the task at hand feel just perfect for online is also a balanced experience with every class acting as checks and balances for each other provoking team success to rely on teams with class diversity and team work along with the best move implementation ever seen in a game just started testing it out online and my kdr is steadily improving as a result ... killzone three is the best fps i have had since the first modern warfare and not once have i even mentioned the obvious ... that this game has dethroned uncharted two and god of war three as the best graphics you can find on the console seriously this game sold my relative who was oblivious to hd not only a new tv but a ps3 as well this game has earned my highest recommendation ... just get it psn poetic 1der

text_review: the changlings produce a form of music that is both modern and medieval it unites a traditional celtic style with modern instruments a middle eastern flair and a deep dark gothic mood the vocals are clear and beautiful ranging from ethereal to haunting the musical backing is very full and complex with every part precisely orchestrated and executed while still producing a freely organic sound it does not just compliment the vocals but seems merges with regeana's voice to form a sound greater than the sum of its parts if you have heard the original changlings cd the only one still available this cd will be familiar but with a much darker undertone the music and vocals are still haunting and will linger in your consciousness long after the music stops i would not consider any of it spooky rather than approaching the mystical unknown it immerses the listener in the dark murky depths of the human experience the album seems to follow only incidentally the theme of a space voyage as though it was only an afterthought individually each song is very strong collectively they are less impressive than they would be without trying to follow the space theme none the less it is definitely a top notch work of art this cd ranks near the top of my list of favorites along with cd's from aenima mirabilis and mercurine

text_review: first things first i loved rainbow six and rogue spear i have also played operation flashpoint quite a bit gr is a combination of the three sort of the good the graphics are astounding enough said tutorial is good no bugs on my system.the bad realism is questionable sure the firefights seem real enough with tracers flying and damage and weapons are realistic however since when do green berets go on missions with one rifle and one secondary weapon answer never they go with seventy pounds of gear including rifles backup pistols several grenades and several types of grenades claymore mines night vision knives explosives radios etc etc they carry anywhere from 300-1000 or more rounds of ammo in gr you get one primary weapon e g m16 and one other thing pistol or explosive or binoculars or grenades but only one of these and you cannot mix and match items in the kit you can only choose from certain combinations e g rifleman use the m16 not m4 or mp5 demo guys use the m4 but not m16 etc second the selection of weapons is poor since when is an elite commando limited in his selection of weapons the second single-player mission is a hostage rescue you have got to rescue two guys from two locations about two hundred yards apart so my first thought was to use a silenced mp5 but it is not available even though they are standard weapons for specops soldiers instead you go with the m16 and when you shoot up one location the enemy elsewhere on the map will not even react or put up their guard in any way even though they would have heard the gunshots.third the friendly ai is pretty limited one reviewer called it user-friendly that is true but it is almost too simple and does not provide the flexibility necessary to simulation special operations warfare you cannot control formations stance or rules of engagement and even with the limited control available the soldiers pretty much suck no aitactics no reaction to the enemy no nothing even though they are supposed to be elite commandos.all in all i expected more from tom clancy and red storm this is basically rainbow six or rogue spear transplanted outside and called a tactical shooter combat sim a lot of potential but i will stick to r6 rs for hostage rescue and ofp for combat sim

text_review: i ordered this bag for my trip to chincha and lima peru hoping i could fit my canon rebel inside ... well ... you can but it is pretty darn snug once you put your other stuff in there and the only lens that fits is a one hundred and five mm if i had brought anything else then i would have had to also carry a camera bag with me which is why i ordered this one hoping i could bypass all the extra stuff to lug about i absolutely have no complaints about this bag it held up during my ten days trudging around really well and i loved all the pockets inside and out i only used the zippered ones on the outside and only in lima's open markets where it was not busy and easy to keep track of where people were but i just want to make this clear this bag is not as big as it looks there is another version of this bag with fewer outside zippers pockets and a different strap which is about ten fifteen cheaper and they are the same size inside keep that in mind when deciding what you think is important while traveling i really did like this purse though and will probably use it for non-travel as well because the strap is so comfy it also was easy to clean off the dirt when i got home

text_review: listening to this album reminds me of how much i miss impetus and transnational speedways those cd's were stolen out of my car not too long ago and i have not gotten around to repurchasing them yet after pitchfork i definitely need to re buy it is really neat to hear tracks from clutch that i have never heard before wicker arcadia etc along with old favs bachanall passive restraints etc and a wink wink from the evolved clutch what would a wookie do etc the raw energy on the reissued tracks really gives a good feel of how intense a live clutch show is raging guitars frantic pounding on the drums and vocals barked out like a madman who just needs to tell you his crazy a story even though clutch has toned down the aggression and vocal effects over the last couple of albums they remain unique and diverse as ever its great to be able to get a different feel from each clutch album that i listen to i can thrash out and bang the steering wheel stomp my feet to the rythm on the old wash board or nod my head to the groove and smile these guys are the sh t if you have not experienced the real deal yet move the mouse up and click buy on as many albums as you can sit back and let the music take you

text_review: background i have two intel macs with aluminum and glass cases one a non-unibody twenty-four inch imac another a unibody 13.3- inch macbook pro they both have core two duo processors and so would not run mac os x 10.7 to a decent level of capability then i heard how apple was going to deprecate the mobileme that i willingly paid one hundred and eighty for so it could stay around for two years now apple is going to throw not just that pittance but the money i spent on three intel macs and a time capsule that did what i wanted to over three thousand out the window so i struck back and keep snow leopard configured in a pleasing manner i am smart about what i do on the internet and like the level of functionality i currently have and decided to supplement my snow leopard with windows seven what version of windows seven deserves to go on an intel mac for me the answer was simple the same version as what i have in snow leopard-not a single missing feature but not installed with objectionable updates which i do not want the mac app store and i do not want a windows app store either so i run windows seven ultimate on my two intel macs with the internet explorer nine and windows seven sp1 hidden and they will stay so as long as absolutely possible with that said here are my opinions of the various features one the new taskbar it kicks butt i had to download the windows seven rc over a 1.5 mbit dsl connection just to experience the new taskbar early and when i got opportunities i bought windows seven that so fat has been fully legal to avoid hassles and yes i know windows seven has windows genuine advantage but if that is going to be an issue i expect that microsoft will inform me of what to do about it the one problem i had was successfully dealt with and they answered another question most kindly my experience has been top notch probably because god gives me better luck i actually pray about things like this and so far god has not failed me two homegroup when all three windows seven computers are on and awake homegroup works perfectly for me i am most pleased with its performance three windows xp mode all three computers have an edition of windows seven that allows it although one does not support virtualization and the unassisted virtualization updater refuses to believe it is needed i use it for microsoft sam and will not be afraid to load applications into windows xp mode should i need them the 13.3- inch core two duo macbook pro has more audio garbling than the imac does the imac has almost none three bitlocker drive encryption i found one nice fellow who posted directions on a way to make bitlocker work without a tpm 1.2 or better chip and it allows me to have access to every feature i paid for i am most pleased with windows seven in that regard four language packs it helps having a laptop and desktop that if i need to can switch languages so i can help people who may need it i have not needed it so far five the geek factor i must say windows seven ultimate gives me great pride that i can have access to not just the basic set of features in home premium but that if someone has a problem with windows seven professional enterprise or ultimate i can help them the features that are also in windows seven professional which i have on an old intel cantrino santa rosa mobile technology former vista laptop that was bought well before the offer to get a free windows seven upgrade but that i used my student thirty offer for-i paid more to get extended download time and a dvd backup plus i got the thirty-two bit version which did not have the installation nightmare of the sixty-four bit version are also so good to have in the toolbox of available windows seven features i love out of the windows seven professional level features network aware printing i go to my aunt and uncle's ginormous house every now and then and my windows seven professional laptop and to be fair my windows seven ultimate macbook pro now too can simply go from the color and black and white laser printers here to my aunt anduncle's officejer j4580 and back again windows seven hoem premium is too little for my dual-cre windows seven computers although i will put it on my emachine-a w3622 with a single core celeron four hundred and twenty at 1.6 ghz and intel gma nine hundred and fifty barely aero-capable graphics plus i can have people who are having windows seven issues send to me for remote assistance and pull their computer up on my imac which has a big enough screen to help most people especially if they have laptops and i can if the problem is not fixable under remote assistance take my macbook pro and have a point of comparison on-site with me especially since i got windows seven from good to great discounts through ebay for windows seven ultimate and microsoft's student offer for windoes seven professional i feel like i got everything i needed for plenty fair enough prices i love the way three or more windows seven computers work with each other i truly do love it i guess i better end this review before i take an eternity plus i saw a commercial on tv that ran a fair amount last year showiing a computer at one person's home being accessed by a laptop that someone let them borrow the remote computer was displaying an aero desktop on the laptop windows vista even ultimate to the best of my knowledge could not do this so i investigated and after months of not knowing i found out that windows seven ultimate with the experience section maxed could do it but professional could not if you love the aero eye candy and especially love windows seven s improvements to it from vista that every bit as much as bitlocker and bitlocker to go or the language packs provided free make windows seven ultimate worth the money over even professional provided your hardware can give you something at least approaching an optimal experience in other words a bloomfield lynnfield clarksdale or arrandale or their sandy bridge successors for those who like them cpus or a core two duo quad or extreme with dedicated or nvidia integrated graphics will be just about perfect for windows seven ultimate and if it can have 5ghz 802.11 n wifi and bluetooth 2.1+ edr or better along with gigabit ethernet and maybe a tpm 1.2 or better chip as well then that is all the better but anyway especially with worthy hardware windows seven ultimate is worth the expense in this user's eye because he has hardware that can come remarkably close to being perfect for windows seven ultimate go microsoft for windows seven you made excellent choices in all but two areas of the windows seven experience windows eight however is as tough a sale as vista was but fora different reason because i do not want my desktop os even on a netbook to be the same as my mobile os and lion faces similar roadblocks from snow leopard update 1-17- two thousand and thirteen i will be updating all of the reviews for all of the windows seven installers i have on tap to reflect a certain difference betweem me and the average reviewer i to date have done all of my installs whether of ultimate full purchase product ultimate upgrade professional upgrade through the windows seven student offer home premium upgrade or home premium upgrade family pack through the clean install method and it never fails to grab all of the updates update to sp1 and then grab the missing post-sp one updates i therefore believe that the people who cannot fully update windows did not do the clean install method and while i do not blame them i do not have the time personally for a system that behaves strangely because windows vista was trying to be transmuted into windows seven when it is hard enough for one service pack of windows seven to be successfully transmuted into another i hope that if you are blaming windows seven for your issues when upgrading from vista that this advice can be of use update 11-21- two thousand and thirteen i since set it up with a third computer in a dell optiplex seven hundred and forty-five so i could experience what it is like on a real pc where it dual boots with xp professional from dell oem installer media asidefrom requiring a custom sound driver for the sound card to support the internal speaker that it has spent all the money on windows seven so now i cannot afford speakers that work it worked perfectly out of the box unfortunately after windows eight hit general availability windows eight gets media center that supports internet tv while that feature was removed from windows seven at microsoft's behest to push eight after finding windows eight does not like to dual-boot with windows seven on hardware that supports uefi i have one of the rare windows seven pcs to support uefi bought a month before windows eight general availability i am now looking at having to sit there and remove my windows seven hard disk to install eight and then manually put the windows seven hard disk back in and pray windows eight has not overwritten my default bios settings that are compatible i want media center to work on windows seven since this is a three hundred and twenty fully legal piece of software when used on computers it was officially activated with on windows seven home premium i really do not care but on windows seven ultimate i want media center and would gladly give up on internet explorer eleven and support of consumer versions to two thousand and twenty windows nine had better be better than eight and as good as seven if not i will buy a used macbook or pro with lion to replace the macbook pro whose fan overstressed so bad that i had to trade it at a loss applecare would not support it if it was not fully up-to-date and i did not want to update to lion that soon given the problem-prone nvidia graphics my older model macbook pro had the seven hundred and forty-five and a pc laptop i bought an upgrade copy of windows seven ultimate for that originally ran home premium vista both work so well but i insist on media center getting full support because with the bad things i have heard on windows eight and even suprisingly bad things for windows 8.1 i want to use windows seven ultimate long after it is internet browsing ability except to activate is gone that is just a rant from someone far too satisfied with windows seven for their own good or so the windows eight fanboys would say i consider myself a windows eight hater because microsoft did not make the right moves as regards windows eight end update 11-21- two thousand and thirteen update 2-3- two thousand and fourteen windows seven is a good os for those people who do not want a mac but do not want windows eight either it does do classic appearance differently from windows vista and earlier instead using the square buttons even in classic appearance but that is ok because i dreamed of an os with this functionality in the taskbar since windows ninety-five and the redesigned taskbar is even in windows seven home premium sure you may lose some of the features in the ultimate edition but you get everything you absolutely have to have-although windows seven anytime upgrade is no longer available to windows seven users so buying the right edition of windows seven is extra-crucial if you buy windows seven home premium and later find out you need xp mode you are going to have to sell your copy of home premium assuming you are using the retail copy and replace it with a retail copy of ultimate or professional windows xp may have been great in two thousand and one but windows seven is as close to xp as you can make vista-and has proven worthwhile ever since two thousand and nine for further proof look at how microsoft released internet explorer ten and eleven for windows seven they sure did not have to do that but they realized windows seven was still popular so popular i have seven copies of it including a family pack of home premium and so they released as many of their updated components as they could for windows seven without totally making windows 8/ 8.1 a non-issue end update 2-3- two thousand and fourteen update 2-27- two thousand included well i sat there and started the backup to this other pc which had received a clean install of windows seven home premium family pack upgrade and office two thousand and three student and teacher edition and it was so easy i knew my money spent on high-end copies of windows seven rather than buying a windows home server which that os later was discontinued was oh so worth it a similar update will be on windows seven ultimate upgrade and windows seven professional upgrade end update 2-27- two thousand and fourteen update 9-16- two thousand and fourteen critical windows nine status text_review: excellent album heres why melody sounds da da da da da .. da da da da da and the words step out the front door like a ghost into a fog window ... and in between the moon and you .. i walk in the air between the rain through myself and back again ... the singer is music's best poet the album is filled with strong sweet seductive waves of color the songs induce a powerful amount of emotion into the listner as you start feeling the way the character of the lyric is feeling the instruments that form the music are pure and the overall production is great the songs are about relationships making it in the music business growing up love happiness faith and sex and god omaha this song was written in omaha about being at a rehabilitaion clinic mr jones was a huge successful hit in the mid 90s even if you are not familiar with the bands music you have probably heard this single a few times rain king ... when i think of heaven deliver me in a black wing bird .. do not try to feed me because i have been here before and i deserve a little more ... i said mama mama mama why am i so alone i cannot go outside i am scared i might not make it home but i am alive ... it is raining in baltimore this is such an eloquent intimate intense song remember to breath during this one and thats all i am gonna say

text_review: we got this after putting up with an obnoxious audio monitor for a year i finally had enough of the static and buzzing so we got this it is perfect for use with one camera the video and sound quality are comparable to much more expensive models but the price is just right unfortunately when we had our second we found that while you can add more cameras to the parent unit there is no way to scan between the cameras it only monitors the camera you are set to we ended up buying the motorola mpb thirty-six with two cameras because it can scan back and forth all night but it does not have vox or the battery life that this unit had i wish this one would scan between the cameras and if they were to make an upgraded version it would be nice to pan zoom and have a temp readout the vox on this is perfect it would light up whenever my daughter cried but never picked up the music or white noise in her room i liked that it clicked a little when it lit up that woke me up but was not annoying the parent unit is a little flimsy feeling but it worked just fine.overall if you only need it for one room this is a wonderful video monitor at a great price

text_review: canon has kept the price of this little gem reasonable i bought it over a year ago and use it more than any other camera it fits nicely in my shirt pocket so i frequently have the camera with me on trips i always carry an extra battery with me because the battery indicator is not very reliable when it falls below full charge it seems to go from half full to zero in no time canon needs to work on this i have a dslr of comparable megapixels that takes slightly better pictures but it is hard to tell without looking at a large print or screen view color reproduction is as accurate as i can tell outdoor especially skin tones are the best i have seen i do not mind the lower level high definition video videos look pretty good on a large tv and unless you are after an academy award you probably will not miss the full one thousand and eighty hd it could use an optical viewfinder because you almost cannot see what you are shooting in full sun unless you shade the display but the optical viewfinder would come at the expense of the ultra compact size and i would rather have the small size also because of the size the controls are tiny and you have to get used to this eventually smart phones will have these photo and video capabilities unless there are large advances in ultra compact digital cameras i think most people will use smart phones instead so they will not have to carry around two gadgets in the meantime i will use this little camera

text_review: 3.5 four stars pros compact it is barely the size of my ear nice looking nice silver finish very high tech lightweight if the ear loop is comfortable for you you could probably wear it for hours cons the directions for set-up are horrific fortunately the motoblu customer service is very good the two people i spoke with had thick accents but they were very knowledgeable and able to walk me through the proper set-up steps fyi i was pairing the h700 with a motorola phone so you think it would be seamless not so once again the directions are very inaccurate i never did get a blue light when i was pairing the phone only purple and i had to hold the call button while opening the boom mic which the directions did not mention oh and like a reviewer stated before the directions point to the small motorola icon on the headset and say this is where the blue light will show it is actually the ring around the call button that lights up this is not a reason to find another headset ... just be prepared it is quite simple to get up and running once you have proper instruction lol and i also got a red light when the headset was charging not a blue one mental note to self call motorola and have them hire different monkey for next version of directions sound is decent but not like talking listening directly from the phone i have not heard other headsets so i cannot say if it is better or worse than another model but it definitely takes a little getting used to on a positive note i asked my friend if he could tell i was on a headset and he said no the ear loop is a little uncomfortable for my ears not big or small just average it is very light but the loop just does not fit great this is most likely going to be different for every person this headset is worth your time but i am not sure i would wantto pay full price for it how and where you get it is up to you hope this info is useful

text_review: i guess i have to be the voice of dissent among these positive reviews i have listened to this recording several times now and do not like it nearly as much as samantha's previous release identity she is going way too far down the smooth jazz road with results that are not pleasant the title track opens with this trend a boring and predictable tune that has little to offer the second track poquita has a nice guitar intro but this leads into the most vapid dancey drum machine-driven junk i have heard in some time please no more of this what follows is an assortment of unoriginal tunes until we get to clouds the stand-out song on the cd this and six of the clock are the best songs on the album samantha is at her best singing more traditional cabaret-style songs and clouds is easily one of her best amazing chord progressions and beautiful melodies interlude is lovely as well though far too short wild is also enjoyable with its unusual rhythmic patterns.finally we have tada yet another remix this is of the title track and all it has is more prominent fake drums plus throughout the album samantha has the occasional annoying tendency to sing slightly sharp this is a problem that has plagued all of her recordings and i suspect it has to do with headphone distortion i have experienced this myself many times in the studio it can be remedied by keeping one headphone off so that the ear hears the voice naturally.so basically sam here is some unsolicited advice lose the drum machine please ditch the less-than-inspiring instrumentals unless like interlude you really have something to say and please no more remixes move more toward the excellent cabaret style you have developed in songs like clouds and like a child and watch your tuning

text_review: just got this today from a big box store in portland i have only been using it for four hours i was going to buy from amazon but for some reason the projected delivery time was three weeks from now that was too long for my purposes i did not want to go apple i wanted at least sixteen gb this is 14.1 gb formatted which is not surprising pros it is teeny tiny it may be smaller than some apple ipod nanos minimal controls but the menus seem to be well thought out you attach it and it is just a drive no itunes crapola to deal with i drag and drop mp3 folders with band album titles and pre-named numbered mp3 file and i am good to go i have microsoft windows seven pro computer operating system i get good sound with my sony mdr three hundred headphones cost 22.50 twenty-four ohms impedance one khzsensitivity db one hundred and two db mw is capable of putting out more volume that i can stand cons file copy is fairly slow but once you do inital setup and copy that is not so bad while it will drive my larger 63ohm sony studio cans headphones it does not produce a good sound with them bass on the larger headphones is weak unsatisfying so i am not using those headphones with this was hoping to do so for plane flight travel the eq is fairly limited five band does not have a lot of precision or major change effect yes it does something it is just kind of minimal the instructions for how to actually fully shut this mp3 player down powered off are a bit cryptic they say it goes into standby it may be that it never shuts off in the normal pull the plug no power sense it is do able you put it on pause and then hold down option button for awhile i guess a better way of saying this is the manual is minimal ___ other info charges by usb to mini-usb male connector two hours for full charge built in non-user replaceable battery overall you get a compact system i will report back later on how long a charge lasts and durability note you can supposedly play back pictures and movies with this it does display the mp3 album graphics fairly clearly i did not buy it for video still display cannot speak to that i have put many albums of mp3s on here and still have 4gb of space remaining if you can swing it buy at least a device with at least 16gb pre-formatted storage that gives you enough to cover a lot of moods genres of music without being forced to delete this to make room for that currently listening to moody blues in search of the lost chord it sounds good satisfying i give this a solid four stars at this time of initial impression ___ update 7/22 two thousand and sixteen i eventually moved onto a fiio x3 ii with a sandisk 128gb sdxc micro-flash card that is 2.7 x the cost of this sony unit but for me it was a must do reason i had so many song files i needed a bigger playground the fiio is in a totally different league and should be i will say the sony got me through earlier times at a reasonable expense

text_review: i purchased two of the cactus v5 sets to use as a remote flash trigger and remote shutter trigger and after eight months i can say the v5 s are absolutely fantastic i have triggered many thousands of photographs and strobe firings and the cactus v5 s have worked flawlessly each and every time.one of the greatest features is each unit is both transmitter or a receiver selected by the power slide switch on the side slide it one way it transmits slide it the other way it receives if you only buy a pair you will not see this as an advantage but for those of us that use more than two its a huge feature providing tremendous flexibility for example i have four v5 s and have used them in the following configurations one v5 set to transmit on camera hot shoe triggering between 1-3 v5 equipped strobes set to receive i can set each flash to a different channel and by changing channel on the transmitter select any individual strobe or by changing to a group channel i can fire them all.yesterday i was firing a complicated setup one v5 in my hand to transmit two v5 set to receive and plugged in to the camera remote shutter port three v5 on my camera hotshoe mount is set to transmit and has a bounce flash daisy chained on top and finally four v5 is set to receive at my umbrella reflector when i press the button on one half way two focuses the camera when i push one button in all the way two trips the camera shutter the camera hotshoe tells three to fire the bounce flash and the flash connected to four i hope that made sense with any other brand to do what i did in my second scenario i would have needed to buy a second transmitter but with my cactus v5 s i just flipped a switch i am going to buy two more to increase the number of flash units i can fire wirelessly and i am considering buying more after that just to keep on hand as spares i expect to be using my v5 s for many many years

text_review: this review is going to be much like my review of the two thousand and nine edition of norton three hundred and sixty because except for the removal of the backup features the two programs are quite alike for the same reason i am not going to be so nice to symantec the makers of norton three hundred and sixty and norton internet security this time around i want to be clear that i am only referring to the windows xp version in this review i may post another one for windows seven users once my new system arrives.the main problem is this you absolutely cannot trust the firewall to work correctly on your system as configured as it is too permissive this means you run the risk of losing valuable personal information and or damaging your computer in the default set it and forget it mode it has continued to fail in almost every firewall test i have thrown at it as it does a horrible job of detecting and blocking potential threats on its own even a free firewall program provided by comodo performs better than norton internet security.the only way to make the firewall safe is to do the following steps one open the norton internet security homepage by doubleclicking on the icon in the system tray two in the box named network click on settings three scroll down to smart firewall click configure next to advanced settings four turn automatic program control off and advanced events monitoring on5 you will get a warning that it is for advanced users congratulations that is what you will become soon six hit apply to accept if your settings are correct it should match the image i uploaded to amazon.from this point forward it will start to ask you before you start a program or access the internet much like the previously referenced comodo firewall it will seem annoying at first however the interruptions will become less frequent as it learns the programs that you have designated as safe you may not recognize each individual file but you can make educated guesses for instance if the file is located in the directory of the program you just started up it is a high probability the file is legitimate because norton has started including file directories in its popup alerts it becomes much easier to locate files you are unsure of from there you can check the properties of the file to make sure they match the program's vendor microsoft or otherwise it just depends on how accepting you want to be after a while the interruptions will become infrequent unless you install something new or more importantly something uninvited is trying to access the internet without your permission it is not a foolproof method by any means but it is much safer than the norton three hundred and sixty and is two thousand and ten default which seems to be to allow anything you run to access the internet and or your computer as long as you perform these steps the firewall performs quite well.fortunately i can say that the antivirus works much better it even identified and quarantined a few of my firewall leaktests before i was able to run them no virus protector is one hundred safe however so the best way to protect your computer is still to practice safe surfing when i deliberately tried to run some questionable files one of them managed to make my computer unbootable and norton never stopped it the same thing happened to norton three hundred and sixty this brings me to another issue i sent that file to symantec months ago with specific details about what it does yet even now norton does not catch it i am starting to wonder how much they are paying attention to the files we send them maybe they are being overrun by the number of people submitting iexplore.exe as a potential virus.the database is still a mess of unnecessary messages that are service related rather than virus related there does seem to be some realization of this so this years version is a little less confusing with links to the database regarding particular issues youmay click on cosmetically norton has changed to yellow over black instead of black over yellow there is a nice buried feature called optimize to get there you need to flip the main menu to the performance history and click a tiny link of the same name not sure why it is tucked away but for this aging system i did notice some improvement in startup times symantec will honor the remaining days of a subscription to a former product and add them to this year's product but you will have to contact them it will also transfer your settings and identity cards and passwords however it will not use your identity card information on new websites per support you need to delete them in spite of the import and start over i also find it takes much longer to login than it did using norton three hundred and sixty almost a 10-15 second wait not sure if that was due to the import or a problem with the program.norton internet security two thousand and ten says on the box that it supports pop three and smtp now for its email scanner that would cover almost every email scanner on the market in symantec's world however that only means outlook and outlook express according to a support guy named kumar he says that in spite of the many popular email programs on the market norton continues to support only outlook and outlook express but he could not really explain why symantec appears to be flat out lying maybe he was stoned i will ask harold next time.one new feature that does not impress me are the constant popups saying i am the first person to run this program or that quite odd considering i get these warnings even after downloading a file from the symantec website you can remove this annoyance by clicking web settings then turning off download insight you have to turn it off completely otherwise it will simply delete any file it considers a risk one of these days symantec will realize we do not like it when they do that.in short this version of norton is not much of an improvement over last year's version and there were a ton of areas where they could have made improvements.lack instead of black over yellow there is a nice buried feature called optimize to get text_review: for starters the toy's display in the box is impressive i would say adrenaline pumping the oversized shark and basic ship design scream open me first at least that is how my almost seven year-old approached it it took about five minutes to fully liberate the toy from its package so you will want to come prepared with scissors or a clipping tool the mega rig pieces are quick connect and easy to take apart and reassemble the almost seven year-old had no problems with assembly and could do everything on his own i needed to consult the instructions to see how the harpoon and crane went together the four 1/2 year-old needed a little help with some of the attachments gets frustrated keeping up with older brother the shark ship comes with several action pieces like the harpoon crane and shark cage along with two characters captain and diver so it is good for imaginative play the happy hum of kids creating their own shark capture stories is music to a busy mother's ears the shark has a moveable jaw so he can swallow objects which are retrieved through a slit in its belly high cool factor for my boys the shark's fins and tail are soft and bendable making them look sharp but not be a safety hazard there are so many combinations the possibilities seem endless there are enough pieces for siblings to share with less quarreling than with a single toy it is a toy my kids come back to play with again and again they even work it into their adventures with lego minifigures and other toys we have not tried--and probably will not try--this toy in water but on land it is excellent

text_review: like many of my pop and dance cds i bought this for one of my dance classes and i actually listen to it outside of class it is poppy cute and fun and the album has some great cuts here are my reviews of the songs one let us go hip-hop meets an irish jig is the only way to describe this it is really short i wanted more 5/52 c'est la vie this was their first single and the only one that did much in the us it is very catchy most likely you will wake up singing it every other day the lyrics and instruments leave something to be desired but hey it is pop at it is best 5/53 rev it up this song is about a car ride it is actually a lot better than it sounds trust me this is an ok song they could definately have done better though 4/54 to you i belong another single it is a ballad and it is kind of sappy but entertaining at the same time it is got some great harmonies and you can hear the irish influence in the background music 5/55 rollercoaster this is as sugar filled as the album gets lyrics like today's the day we are out to play make this a cheesy classic it was another single from the album it is upbeat and cheery and undeneiably catchy but it lacks substance and maturity 4/56 blame it on the weatherman ummm . . . this is very weird and is one of those tracks where you have to listen to it several times before you start to like it it was their fourth single and a huge hit in europe 3.5 fifty-seven we four girls ok girls this is b witched not korn this song would be awesome recorded by another group but with four twentysomething irish girls with really high voices it sounds kind of strange 2/58 castles in the air this is one of their better slow songs good vocals a pleasant tune definately listenable this might appeal to older listeners more than younger though 5/59 freak out wahoo this is a great danceable track i really love the intro and the voices are just great once again horrible lyrics platorm shoes too high for hip-hop but that just adds to the fun 5/510 like the rose this is b witched being really mature this is a beautiful ballad that can bring tears to anybodies eyes actually i have no clue what it is about but it is still got a beautiful melody and is a nice slow song it is my favorite on the album five five hundred and eleven never giving up this is my second favorite track on the album it is upbeat and sugary without being too childish it is got a great beat and is very danceable it really should have been released 5/512 oh mr.postman um no just read the title 1/5 overall this is a great fun album no matter what age you will not be able to resist b witched's charm it is such a blast to find a band that is one hundred happy instead of a lot of the depressing music played today

text_review: i have had this vacuum for almost a year now picked it up from walmart for less than available online i have never needed to contact the manufacturer for support but based on the reviews i read that sounds like it would be a waste of time when this vacuum dies i will happily go out and buy another one of the same model if it is still available here is why ... light weight easy to empty easy to clean exceptional dust pick up best value of any vacuum i have ever owned wife never complains to me about it being too heavy the design and engineering of this vacuum is impressive they have made it so easy to take apart and clean the chambers and filters no tools everything just snaps together with precession that makes me smile every time i clean it i brought it because of the price and five year warranty but i would gladly pay this much money every year to have such a marvelous machine of course it is made of plastic but my 500lb hoover was too and every plastic part on it cracked and fell off during it is short life i paid twice as much for the hoover and the replacement parts for the hoover were going to cost me as much as this shark vacuum if this vacuum lasts for five years i will be amazed but i will not be disappointed if it does not and i will not waste my time trying to get it repaired .. i will keep it for spare parts and happily go out and buy a new one because it is such a great value

text_review: when i got my xbox it came with a copy of sega two thousand gt i really enjoyed that game up to a point namely the point when the difficulty curve shot up dramatically and it was no longer fun to play anymore i e impossible to win forza is light-years beyond that game and i am sure most other games in this genre the learning curve is gradual and you actually end up learning a great deal about auto racing yes it is that real it is a true simulation not just a game there is a massive selection of cars and tracks and many different types of competition events career mode is the most fun as you can win cars and money and spend that money to customize your cars do not spend too much time tricking out your cars though because you will find yourself switching between cars frequently in order to get through all of the different events this can be a real learning experience if you have spent the majority of your time in a fwd car switching to the rwd can be traumatic try the porsche nine hundred and eleven a-class at laguna seca or enter the rotary challenge and try to keep that rx7 on the track luckily there is a free run mode in which you can practice with any car on any track an invaluable aid when you find yourself stumped you can tweak each car's setup right down to the tire pressure spring tension wheel camber gear ratios and all that stuff you really can get lost in this game overall this is a game which will remain interesting for quite some time not good news for your family or any hobbies you will end up neglecting for hours on end i am beginning to hate this game because it is so dang fun i just cannot stop playing darn you microsoft

text_review: i see references to pink floyd here because of mr gilmour's involvement of course ... but what i just listened to was a dance mix with booming bass beats and music mixed so low in the sound-field that you could not hear much other than those beats you can just about hear david gilmour's guitar over the beats and once in a while something ping-pongs around the speakers crunching sounds inaudible voices etc when the music is more ambient and chilled it seems to never settle into anything at one point an acoustic guitar piece is cut-up into a jittery mess that never comes into focus except for a few seconds before it fades into another phase of this unsettled album for me that is what is wrong here ... even david gilmour's guitar never ever becomes anything but background for more overwhelmingly bass-toned beats maybe the 3d mix will reveal more ... if i ever feel like buying this again to find-out sorry all you others out there but this does not even come close to any of the other orb albums i own maybe i expected more of a floating ambient album ... maybe i will get used to what this is and love it in a few plays but right now it is all too dance beat oriented for me ... and too little ever jells here to say that you have even heard much more than sound-effects under a beat to me david gilmour's guitar should be heard as more than just sound-effects hell maybe my disc is defective seeing how much others love this i cannot say i am happy with it

text_review: these are the best headphones i have ever used not that i am a serious audiophile i have had them only about a week but already i have found them very enjoyable i have also used the slightly cheaper closed-back hd two hundred and eighty pros plus tons of various junky cheap headphones the 558s have an excellent sound stage thanks to the open back design listening to music feels like you are sitting in the middle of the orchestra or face-to-face with the lead singer of a band extremely accurate across most of the audio spectrum there is a slight hump in 5-10 k frequencies which means sounds just over typical vocal range are slightly exaggerated bass is accurate but not excessive you are not going to get noticeably better sound for less than double the price these are excellent for listening to all genres of music and for gaming which are my primary uses.you will definitely need a decent headphone amp if you use these with a phone ipod etc or any other output that is not solidly powered this is by design these are not cheap flimsy drivers accuracy requires power when it comes to headphones they sound pretty poor on my un-amped galaxy nexus and only a little better on my iphone four without a headphone amp i am still waiting on delivery of the portable amp i ordered but most people say they sound excellent when properly driven on my desktop computer they sound fantastic even on integrated motherboard sound granted i have a high-end motherboard with a better than average sound system built in i would recommend getting a shorter replacement cord with a 3.5 mm jack the cord is very easy to remove with the twist-lock but will not fall out on accident the standard cord is extremely long not a problem for stationary use but it is poorly suited for portable listening.overall i can highly recommend these headphones to anyone looking for an affordable entry into high-quality audio

text_review: daft punk is one of my all time favorites their four singles and video series for them were genius and amazing but three stars was probably generous for this cd because it disappointed me a little i am still confused about whether they are treating this as a new album since it was so marketed in the us unlike alive one thousand , nine hundred and ninety-seven if they are it was a dissapointment if it was meant to be a bunch of extended clublike versions of their previous songs then it is alright dont get me wrong the only new songs on the album ouverture and aerodynamite are great and distinct style like discovery daft punk but the club mixes and experimental songs i could do without parts of the club mixes are great but they repeat and run on like an average techno song something i have never known daft punk for the american influence is clear on this album too with the presence of rap on the neptunes remix and slum village both songs are terrible and i try to forget that aerodynamic was destroyed and rap put over it i also have to mention that the romanthony version of one more time is possibly the worst song i ever heard and i am quite surprised its even on the cd with how bad the singing is artists change but this wasnt change it just kinda seemed like they were trying to get you to spend money to top it off i thought i would finally have access to their website only people who buy their cds can go there and when i loaded the cd it took me to a webpage advertising their interstella five hundred and fifty-five figurines forcing me to sign up for some advertising scheme for it kinda disappointed but im trying to tell myself this was just to hold us over for now

text_review: well i have to say that if you are considering a an online rpg then ac is one of the better ones if not the best however there is one very important factor which has forced myself and quite a few other to leave the game the problem was not with the game itself it is as addictive as they come but instead lay with the technical side of the game the first big problem was with the game server downtime ac goes down regualarly for three hours each day this time is as you would guess during the off-peak hours of the day which is great if you live in the us however for international players guess again this was not the problem which caused me to cancel my membership however it was after i switched from a telephone connection to a cable tv connection that i became locked out of the server i spent a good four weeks trying to get any kind of technical support from ac and microsoft my search for help included four chat rooms and over twenty letters sent to two support email addresses i never once met a systems operator who did not reffer me elsewhere nor did i ever get a single reply to the e-mails i sent the bottom line is microsoft will not be able to help you if you have problems they will send you to a seperate ac support center the ac support center exsists but will unfortunately ignore you so if you have worries about system compatibility or a non-telephone internet connection especially through a cable tv line it might be safer to go with everquest or ultima i would have liked to be able to have words with the support team about this but alas could not find one

text_review: okay so the heavy metal cartoon has not aged well the soundtrack fares a lot better once you get past the fact that aside from a few tunes such as sabbath's mob rules there is not a whole lot of heavy metal music here instead most of the songs on the cd are better thought of as late 1970s fm rock songs this is the type of music aor used to play before it mutated into classic rock and stopped playing anything recorded after one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-three all of the songs here are vaguely trippy hard rock some with fusion aspirations and some trying out for progressive it is fitting music because the original heavy metal magazine was full of post one thousand , nine hundred and seventy psychedelic artwork strong points include journey's best ballad open arms blue oyster cult's veteran of the psychic wars a couple of former eagle don felder songs and cheap trick's reach out the heavier side is represented by sammy hagar sabbath and grand funk railroad i have no idea how devo got in here and i wish they did not for the most part however this is a very solid cd music like this was swept aside by punk on the one hand and mtv on the other at least until trip hop managed to sneak some of the laid-back grooviness in through the back door

text_review: if like me a few months ago you have a 76cs and are wondering whether to replace it with the 76csx i recommend doing so.the 76csx is surprisingly improved over the 76cs i noticed that . . . . one the antenna is much stronger the 76csx pulls in satellite signals inside my house two the annoying hold level warning on the compass page no longer appears i guess garmin has solved that issue three the batteries stay in place even with severe use in my case on the handlebar of my mountain bike as i traverse rough terrain with the 76cs and 76s i had to install bubble wrap inside the battery cover to get the batteries to stay in contact on the 76csx the batteries have not dislodged to extract them i have found it is better to roll them out than to try to pull them out four the unit will draw power from your computer via the usb cable.in sum i am very glad that i bought the 76csx and sold my 76cs i have one suggestion the screen could easily be scratched on my prior garmin gps receivers this time before venturing out of the house with the 76csx i overlaid a clear plastic invisibleshield film that i had bought from a company called zagg on my very first outing i crashed my bike flying through some sharp branches and twigs the screen was unblemished
