text_review: a particularly strong debut for the san fransisco based combo this five piece band greg yanito guitar and vocals eric reedy string bass and vocals bill mckenna electric guitar mikiya matsuda steel guitar billy zelinski drums rips through a set a good ol country music both yanito and reedy sing and compose and they know how to write songs that sound like little classics which also keeps the set varied you will only find two covers gene o'quinn's texas boogie and carl smith's back up buddy smith being an obvious influence on the band.carl sonny leyland sits in and plays piano on four tracks adding a good dose of country boogie and even rock'n'roll pretty baby to the mix there is also some country swing duckin and dodgin a bit of bakersfield women and wine sweet little things and a superb hank williams influenced number trouble free state of mind it is tastefully produced by lee jeffriess and you can hear his touch on some steel guitar guitar arrangements reminiscent of his work with ashley kingman in the fly rite boys.if carl smith hank williams merrill moore wayne hancock big sandy are sweet words to your ears be sure to add the b-stars to your list and it is not only a pleasure for your ears but also for the eyes as it comes in a nicely designed digipack.fred turgis jumpin from six to six

text_review: i have tried the steam-type humidifiers evaporative types mechanical rotary sling-types devilbiss and ultrasonic units they all have their ups and downs but this is the best one i have ever used it is also the most expensive but the value is good because of its good design ultrasonics need water with low minerals or else you will get white dust municipal water might be ok but mine is not if you have well water you will definitely need the mineral reduction cartridge it eliminates the white dust for me entirely the puck-shaped carbon cartridges that go in the water tank also help to reduce the chlorine smell from city water together with the pre-heater quiet fan and very good flexible controls standard on this unit it is a very manageable and predictable humidifier i have used the air-o-swiss ez-cal cleaner for it so far and cleaned it well after the cleaning light went on and it cleaned the unit just fine the heater helps to evaporate the mist more quickly but you may still find you need to keep the unit higher up on a stand to prevent a small damp area on your floor i fill it twice a day and it runs non-stop at the top setting in my house because i have a large area to cover i would recommend it for the area suggested in the listing about 500-650 sq feet max they are pricey but good so if you have a larger area you may need more than one

text_review: this is an excellent neil young album which is a relief to be able to say because i did not think much of americana his last one this album like americana features crazy horse but is a completely different piece of work and it is terrific in places i think it comes close to his best which makes it something really special.the overall sound and feel is vintage neil young there are the hauntingly melancholy tunes the thoughtful quirky lyrics and the great chord sequences which made albums like harvest and after the goldrush so great combined with the controlled distortion-driven power of the brilliant rust never sleeps am i showing my age here this album is also a reminder of what a great band crazy horse are the sound is terrific there is some great guitar work and they are tight and gutsy so even born in ontario the only slightly weak song on the album still sounds really good.neil young is often meditating on experience and aging here but he still sounds young and fresh and still has more power and guts than a lot of artists half his age several of the tracks are very long driftin back lasts nearly half an hour and other tracks are over fifteen minutes this of course is typical neil young refusing to bow to convention and doing whatever makes musical sense to him at the time he has always done this and it can be dreadful it sometimes has been in the past but nearly all the time here it is great the huge ramada inn is a masterpiece in my view and more conventional shorter tracks like twisted road may well end up in the list of neil young classics.there is little self-indulgence and a huge amount of real musical substance driftin back could perhaps do with a little trimming but it is still a really good track the last half of walk like a giant will probably get the skip-to-next treatment from me but its first eight minutes or so are quite brilliant.you have to hand it to the man he does not mess about and within six months of releasing the mediocre americana he has come up with a real cracker which i think will stand among his finest albums if you are not already familiar with neil young this may not be the best place to start but if you are i suspect that like me you will love this very very warmly recommended t mess about and within six months of releasing the mediocre americana he has come up with a real cracker which i think will stand among his finest albums if you are not already familiar with neil young this may not be the best place to start but if you are i suspect that like me you will love this very very warmly text_review: if you are in the market for screenwriting software do not buy movie magic screenwriter version six i have used movie magic since the ninety s it is fundamentally a great tool for writing screenplays and i have written several using it however the reason you should not buy it is because this company does not seem to be putting anymore money into updates the windows version is buggy beyond belief and i have been waiting for an update from version 6.0 5.89 for years there are no definitive answers to when an update will be available and frankly it is irrelevant at this point because there are far more inexpensive options that do the job and do it well the fact of the matter is you do not need all the bells and whistles this program offers and the price point reflects a time when this and final draft were the only game in town that was ten years ago now the price is ridiculously over-inflated when you consider the competition especially for a program that cannot function bug-free in a windows 7,8 8.1 environment no tech support updates no purchase no recommendation

text_review: well i like small portable flashes i have gone through a few sunpak one hundred and twenty-one s they are really cheap so i do not mind and contemplated a leica sf or contax tla two hundred flash which both use awkward batteries eventually this fuji flash came out promising to be compact with good build quality and manual controls i found one slightly used on ebay i have a x100 though my primary camera is a mamiya seven medium format film camera.pros awesome build quality seems to match the x-pro one and certainly does fine on my x100 takes aaas ... not quite as convenient as aas but still a lot better than those crazy batteries that other similar flashes take ttl metering on the fuji cameras is quite good though i use it mostly on manual controlling the flash is a breeze for this i would give it five stars really excellent and easy to switch between manual and ttl it works really conveniently as an off-camera flash triggered by your camera's built-in flash i love this feature my old nikon dslr had it and i cannot wait to use it more with the fuji although i suppose with a hotshoe extension cord you could retain ttl like the nikon somehow had comes with a leather case and a little tripod adapter as it should for over two hundred both nicely made it locks into the fujis with a little button release ... very nice feature it seems to still mount on all other cameras though it will not lock into the hotshoe.cons like most of the x100 s controls the exposure dial on the ef-x twenty is very loose and prone to being moved accidentally it is a little bit too big for the x100 from the photos i have seen it looks pretty balanced on the x-pro one and it feels like nothing on my mamiya seven but on the x100 it is a little heavy compared to the camera the auto-startup and shutdown when you turn off the camera the flash turns off too okay cool but if the camera is on and the flash is off and you try to turn the flash on itwill start up for about a quarter of a second and then just go back off after six or seven times of this it will finally stay on if the flash is already on and then you turn on the camera the flash will go off i am not sure if my unit is defective but that is pretty annoying i discovered that if you turn them both on at the same time they work.overall this flash functions pretty well on the fuji cameras once you get it turned on i really wish this flash had an auto setting with a mini exposure chart on the back like the sunpaks do they can be used with any camera really easily i guess if you only shoot digital manual mode is a fine alternative i use it plenty on film too is it the perfect flash for any camera it is just okay for that it is really small and portable much stronger and higher up than the x100 lemmas: well i like small portable flash i have go through a few sunpak one hundred and twenty-one s they be really cheap so i do not mind and contemplate a leica sf or contax tla two hundred flash which both use awkward battery eventually this fuji flash come out promising to be compact with good build quality and manual control i find one slightly use on ebay i have a x100 though my primary camera be a mamiya seven medium format film camera.pros awesome build quality seem to match the x-pro one and certainly do fine on my x100 take aaa ... not quite as convenient as aa but still a lot better than those crazy battery that other similar flash take ttl metering on the fuji camera be quite good though i use it mostly on manual control the flash be a breeze for this i would give it five star really excellent and easy to switch between manual and ttl it work really conveniently as a off-camera flash trigger by you camera 's built-in flash i love this feature my old nikon dslr have it and i can not wait to use it more with the fuji although i suppose with a hotshoe extension cord you could retain ttl like the nikon somehow have come with a leather case and a little tripod adapter as it should for over two hundred both nicely make it lock into the fuji with a little button release ... very nice feature it seem to still mount on all other camera though it will not lock into the hotshoe.cons like most of the x100 be control the exposure dial on the ef-x twenty be very loose and prone to be move accidentally it be a little bit too big for the x100 from the photo i have see it look pretty balance on the x-pro one and it feel like nothing on my mamiya seven but on the x100 it be a little heavy compare to the camera the auto-startup and shutdown when you turn off the camera the flash turn off too okay cool but if the camera be on and the flash be off and you try to turn the flash on itwill start up for about a quarter of a second and then just go back off after six or seven time of this it will finally stay on if the flash be already on and then you turn on the camera the flash will go off i be not sure if my unit be defective but that be pretty annoying i discover that if you turn they both on at the same time they work.overall this flash function pretty well on the fuji camera once you get it turn on i really wish this flash have a auto setting with a mini exposure chart on the back like the sunpak do they can be use with any camera really easily i guess if you only shoot digital manual mode be a fine alternative i use it plenty on film too be it the perfect flash for any camera it be just okay for that it be really small and portable much stronger and higher up than the x100 be flash and would make a good addition to any kit i use flash a lot and this one be probably the best option for the x100 and x-pro one unless you need to be bounce light

text_review: i like puzzles that make sense and these did you push a button you see the result without having to hunt around for what is going on for example in mysterious journey two there is several puzzles where you have to form a circuit or connect one side of a grid to another by clicking on dials ... very straight-forward puzzles draw the grids out and it is not difficult to work out on paper in another you find your way across a fog enshrouded pathway very cool by plotting the path from below.while there is very little having to combine information from several sources to figure out a puzzle it does occur once or twice druing the main part of the game and again at the end and there is a few math-based puzzles too in varying degrees of difficulty hey that is what universal hint system is for still gamers with more experience than i might not have much problem wtih them.an earlier reviewer mentioned that half the time a puzzle led to nothing just an area to look out of i am not sure where the reviewer is referring to but i did not find that to be true you open a door and there is something to find learn about in a cut-scene see or do behind it.the storyline is interesting and well developed and the ending is satisfying.as far as graphics i am not a tech person but i found them to be very pretty i wish i could have roamed a bit more in a few places the graphics looked just too inviting to simply view from afar the landscape is filled with bright colors and intriguing designs this is not click and point so you are able to move about freely.the music is not great but at least it does not detract from the game the voices are fine a cut above most games the mechanical voices are done with a bit of special effects a nice touch the computer-rendered people move fairly naturally you have little control over settings but in my experience the game ran fine athlon 64x2 geforce 7600gs i wish there were more games like this puzzles clues that are scattered hither and yon only to make little sense is not my idea of fun i would recommend mysterious journey two to anyone who wants an easier game that does not over-tax their brain.rce 7600gs i easier game that does not over-tax their brain

text_review: i am rather ashamed to admit that though i have always respected her obvious musical talent from afar i would somehow managed to escape fiona's charms all these years ... until the other night when i could not resist any longer after being intrigued enough by the samples i would heard here and on her myspace page i purchased the idler wheel ... that same night and proceeded to listen to it three times straight through the first time i was bewildered by what i was hearing as it was difficult for me to connect with in the same way it is difficult for me to connect with the avant-garde jazz of john coltrane or thelonious monk even though i could definitely appreciate the artistry involved in the music's construction the second time it all made a little more sense but i still was not totally feeling it toward the end of my third listen however i realized my cheeks were starting to hurt i would been smiling from ear to ear for about a good thirty minutes straight.this is an album that works so perfectly as a whole work of art it is hard for me to cite specific highlights most of the songs are dependent on the ebbs and flows of what came before to have its maximum effect so i definitely recommend listening to this album straight through a few times or at least in large chunks before deciding this is not your thing like some fans are saying as a fan of more guitar-driven rock it is not really my thing either or so i thought then i just put my headphones on let go of all my preconceived notions of what it should sound like and let fiona bring me into her world a world that to me is almost like some weird parallel-dimension 1940s in which she is the billie holiday of that reality only one who plays a mean piano with odd time-signatures curlicue melodies household object-based percussion and insanely varied vocals and lyrics that make you feel her wide spectrum of emotions even if you do not quite fully understand them.fiona can go from singing about love to anger to sorrow to despair to paranoia to neon zebras within the span of a couple songs and the result is intoxicating if you just give in to it and let her take you there her voice ranges from angelic to maniacal and everything in between sometimes all within the same song leaving me feeling almost exhausted at times but by the time i get to the excellent kaleidoscopic and insane hot knife which closes the album i am usually ready to take another ride the production on the album is very sparse with rarely more than piano and percussion framing fiona's voice but that only helps magnify the range and authenticity of emotion coming out of her and the result is as close to perfection as i am likely to hear this year or any year the idler wheel ... is not always an easy fun ride but i can almost guarantee that if you let it it will be a fulfilling one there is no higher compliment i can give than that it is not impenetrable some works of art are just deeper and take longer to sink in and those are the ones that tend to stick with you longer and affect you more profoundly this album will one day be considered a masterpiece i am sure but i am just thankful to have finally discovered her beautiful work even if i am about a decade and a half late hopefully she does not take another seven years to resurface next time though thankfully i will have a few new-to-me old albums of hers to tide me over in the meantime and i am sure that if her next album is anywhere near as brilliant and inspiring as this one the wait will definitely have been worth it the live dvd included with the deluxe version is very high-quality and well worth spending the extra cash for as fiona is in top form at least as far as i can tell considering i am a fiona apple newbie

text_review: not knowing any better we inadvertently purchased a booster seat that you just placed in the seat of the vehicle and then strapped the child in with the vehicle's seat belt what a mistake from the beginning my husband was not real happy with it because of the way the booster seat would move around and the way our son could scoot himself down in the seat and sometimes put the shoulder strap under his arm we never really felt like he was properly seated in it when someone emailed us a video showing the dangers of a booster seat such as ours that is not tethered in like a car seat with a five point harness system we were convinced and immediately purchased this booster seat this booster seat is well worth every penny it may take some work getting it strapped in the seat of the vehicle correctly but once it is in the right way it does not budge and the five-point harness system gives us the peace of knowing that our son is securely in the seat and not able to move around yet at the same time it is very comfortable and he has no problem sleeping in it without his head flopping around we are thrilled with this seat

text_review: well after reading all the great reviews on these headpohones i decided to give them a try as i feared they are a gimmick these headphones have a vibrating thing that sits on the back of your neck while it is designed to simulate the heavy bass of a real home theater system it ended up making me shake my head both uncontrollably and because i feel like such a sucker for purchasing these things the shaking mechanism produces no actual sound of bass just a rythmic pulsing sounds cool it is not and to top it all off the headphones are rather uncomfortable i do not recommend these for long listening sessions but their bulky clumsy design makes them difficult to walk even a short distance with so sitting down seems to be the only venue for listening to be fair however these headphones produce some fairly decent sound midrange sound seems almost absent however and everyhing seems to have a slightly high pitch to it with the vmss bass system turned off the drivers still manage to produce some decent bass but not enough that i would justify the ... price tag and the so-so mid and high range sound is nothing to die for either and for the aesthetically-conscious teen like myself these headphones look absolutely horrid i do not think i would walk around with them unless i was in my grandmother's nursing home in short if you want to buy into a gimmicky product then go ahead and purchase the brain shaker extreme headphones but if you are like me and you want a pair of portable decent-sounding phones look elsewhere

text_review: i installed premier two thousand and fifteen every thing seems to have worked fine the program backed up my earlier version files fine and converted fine amazon shows that quicken will update fine from two thousand and ten forward i updated from two thousand and nine and i do not see any problems but will have to look further but on first glance seems ok i decided to upgrade since i have not changed in a number of years product reviews sometimes reflect the experience or lack thereof of the user i am reasonably computer knowledgeable and am pleased with the program so far will update going forward if any problems pop up but starting out quicken premier has worked well i use turbotax every year everyone knows the problem this year with the change in deluxe luckily intuit did follow through with the free upgrade to premier where necessary in my opinion intuit could be a lot more user friendly going forward have spent some time putting in accounts and had some trouble with update five but backing up and reinstalling was effective and the update worked fine i see now that update six has caused problems and quicken took it off their servers until they can fix the update i think the program code could probably be better i would guess it is smart to hold off on patches when they are first released any new code can cause unexpected problems quicken is no different too much reworking and yearly updates to get may be a negative but overall the program is working for me it does not handle every transaction well i had difficulty putting in ee bonds there seems to be no simple way to set it up and have it track interest still i am reasonably satisfied but could always be better i know many are frustrated but it would seem to be difficult for any program to handle so many different transactions 5/11 fifteen update update quicken's update five which was installed with a popup dialogue box caused the program to lose some functionality i deleted the program under windows programs and features and then used quicken's clean ui to further clean the program from the computer i originally used just quicken's clean ui but that did not work by itself so the reinstall text_review: several years ago i picked up a used copy of this at videogame store and i was surprised by how much i enjoyed it to tell the truth i would never even seen most of the wrestlers on the game but i still thought it was very cool the wrestlers did and do look kind of cartoonish but i did not and do not care about that the game is a bit slow but that did not really bother me either i played it a lot the part of the game that i enjoyed most was the create-a-legend mode this was the first wrestling game that i would played where you could actually assign your created wrestlers all of their own moves as opposed to having to give them move-sets of existing wrestlers like you had to on another wrestling game or two that i would played before this one i thought it was fun to play as my wrestlers and open up new moves that i could give them i have got created wrestlers on two three memory cards the maximum number you can have on each of them i also enjoyed playing the referee and watching the computer wrestle i only ever opened like one or two of the locked wrestlers and thus never finished the career mode but i never cared that much this game does not seem to be very loved at least not by reviewers at this site but i thought it was one of the best wrestling games i would ever played in fact i still think it is one of the best i have ever played even though i have not actually played it in quite a while now i thought it was about time this game got another good review and a little more love

necessary theypointed me to my laptop manufacturer's website ... and told me that the support page there would have the latest bluetoothdrivers.this was not exactly correct there were no updates to the bluetooth drivers on this page but there was an update to the bluetoothmanagement application when i downloaded and installed that update the headset successfully paired and i have been using it withan ip phone application on my laptop so far so go the quality is acceptable and the range seems to be good i was evenable to pair it with a second device droid maxx although i have yet to use it with that device let alone answer calls or switchbetween devices using it with a second device was a bit tricky the document did not help much but i think the basic idea is to paireach device separately with the other bluetooth turned off turn everything off and then turn everything back on again and then wait.eventually both devices found the headset and connected i will update this review again after i use it some more beware win seven driver issues sent a link that wants more money to get the right driver the above rating is temporary until the issue i am having is resolved i just received the headset and tried to pair it with my win seven sixty-four bit laptop after the device was recognized by my bluetooth manager it told me that it need to find and update the drivers for the device so i let windows do that it came back and said that it could not update the driver and to contact the manufacturer so i did they responded within a day and sent me alink supposed pointing to the proper drivers in reality the link pointed to an application called drivertuner which scans the laptop and find all the out-of-date drivers i keep my drivers up to date religiously so this got me suspicious so i selected just the bt driver for the headset and told it to download that it still attempted to download all the out-of-date drivers worse in order to finish the job it told me i had to register this copy of drivertuner which by the way is installed itself as a auto-starting system tray app even though i explicitly unchecked the box telling it to do that during installation even worse still in order to register took me to a webpage asking thirty for the license key at that point i had enough exited the webpage and the app which i had to do twice because it minimized itself to the tray and attempted to uninstall the app even that did not go smoothly i had to hunt down and manually delete all the leftovers the uninstaller could not remove needless to say i ran my virus scanner afterwards i have sent a followup to taotronics asking them to simply send me the necessary driver and told them i did not wish to pay an additional thirty to get this headset working.if they send me the right driver and it installs without further funny business i will update this and review the headset itself otherwise amazon will be getting a return and i will not buy another taotronics product again

text_review: simon rattle has recorded a lot of 19th century music and most of the results have been dismal there is little to recommend by rattle in pre 20th century repertoire a few haydn symphonies some pretty good brahms bits of mahler ein heldenleben by strauss which is just at the cusp of the 20th century alright so rattle is not the conductor to go to for the great classics however when he records modern music he seems fully in tune with it is sound and style plus he has less competition on the market to boot here is a collection from a trio of composers that seem forever destined to be tough nuts to crack as far as their music being loved and achieving mass exposure they are never going to achieve popularity at the same time anyone with an open mind and open ears can be enthralled by the works contained here schoenberg's creepy mysterious five orchestral pieces webern's ethereal and far more compact six orchestral pieces rattle plays them all with nuance and feeling the real reason i bought this disc is the lulu suite and it is a breathtaking haunting compilation from berg's great modern opera arleen auger is the soprano soloist and she scores great on all accounts her contribution is limited to two tracks so people who are afraid of operatic singing need not worry rattle and his burmingham orchestra are the true stars comparing directly rattle's take on the lulu suite against abbado's with the lso on dg i consistently find rattle more involved more refined and sharper when the music needs more violence the digital recording by emi is also expert and scores over dg's analogue sound for abbado which lacks some atmosphere rattle made this record back in 1987-88 and it stands up to any competition on the market

text_review: it has its issues for a game to be good i have one requirement do i get angry when playing it i can honestly say that at no time have i gotten angry while playing to give an example of what annoys me to no end when playing an fps in cod ghosts if i join a game in progress i will spawn into the game directly in front of an enemy player if i join in a game in progress i will be on a team that is already well behind the winning team score with no chance of making a comeback rage quitting hosts constantly one out of every three spawns will put me in front of an enemy cod players in general.in battlefield depending on the game mode i can choose when and where i spawn if someone rage quits who cares the game is server hosted a badass player on your team in battlefield with an insane kill count did it with skill tactics and teamwork not with a killstreak reward.there are bugs there are issues the bugs are annoying because if you played medal of honor warfighter it had these bugs as well i know dice only developed the engine for warfighter but it does not change the fact that these bugs exist in both games the issues are mainly with the battlelog service on the three hundred and sixty and one it seems to be down constantly this prevents your loadouts from being available to at times being unable to join a game.dice is an awesome company and i truly believe that in the near future my problems will become moot.also remember even if infinity ward manages to balance ghosts their community is still the largest collection of dbags in gaming

text_review: to compare this to other units you need to evaluate surge suppression ratings in both joules and amps as well as look at the clamping voltage when you add it all up this is the best protection you can get for the money.this tripp lite unit has a very high surge suppression rating 3,300 joules /8 5,000 amps you will not find many surge protectors with this high a combined rating it also has a one hundred and forty volt clamping voltage this means that it goes into action when the voltage spikes just a little higher than the normal one hundred and twenty volts in your line some units have higher clamping voltages some in the three hundred volt range which means they are not as effective with clamping voltage the lower the better as long as it is above the normal line voltage one hundred and forty volts is ideal you have to go to the tripp lite site to find the clamping voltage specification it also comes in a sturdy metal box which means it will not melt as plastic will if it suffers an energy surge i bought this to protect the refrigerator in my new kitchen if you have a modern built-in kitchen you may not have space between the wall and refrigerator to mount a surge protector i found space behind the slide out garbage bin which is right next to the fridge and drilled a hole in the side wall of the cabinet for the power cords you can probably find some such fix if your set-up is tight it is worth it for the peace of mind

text_review: david greilsammer is an artist worthy of attention his ability to touch the keyboard of a modern steinway piano and make us believe we are sitting in a salon in mozart's day so characteristic of the style the embellishments and the cadenzas that even on a modern instrument have all the grace and clarity of the original harpsichord performances here he performs with the conductor-less suedama ensemble a student orchestra based out of the 92nd street y in new york city of which greilsammer is musical director the concerti selected for this very well recorded cd include no five in d major k one hundred and seventy-five no six in b flat major k two hundred and thirty-eight and no eight in c major k two hundred and forty-six we can only hope that this foray into the rarely performed concerti continues on subsequent cds.greilsammer and his ensemble offer vivid frolicking and when called for very soul searching performances greilsammer uses his own cadenzas and for once they sound more like mozart than most other soloist-written cadenzas there are moments in these three works that suggest the seeds of some of mozart's symphonies and operas were already planted hearing these early works written as a teenager offers the listener a deeper appreciation for what was to follow in mozart's prodigious output david greilsammer is rapidly becoming a champion for taking risks in music and we are fortunate for his arrival on the artistic scene grady harp january eleven

text_review: truly amazing camera i own several dslr cameras with some of the best lenses out there in order to capture all our memories photography is my hobby so i know a thing or two when i see a great shot i needed a small camera to carry with me everywhere so i purchased several but after trying them out they all went back to where they came from until i got my hands on this canon n100 i am very very picky about picture quality so none satisfied this expectation with the exception of this camera i was aware that it is impossible for a small camera to produce professional picture quality but i can safely say this camera bit the odds and took me by surprise it even produces the 3d effect with the blurred background that could only be obtained by dslr cameras with expensive lenses all settings are wonderful on this camera but after using it for almost a year i find myself preferring the auto setting when taking pictures of groups of people because this is the setting that brings everything in the picture into focus and then my most favorite and my mostly used setting is the background defocus this is the one creating the 3d effect with blur the farther the background is from your subject the more blur will be noticed there are two ways to do this once you have selected this setting you can press the shutter or you can touch the screen which is touch sensitive you will not obtain the same result if you touch the screen the spot where the screen has been touched will be the only one truly focused so the rest will be blurred out if you use the shutter button the camera will automatically focus on the face and the rest will be blurred more or less depending how far or close it is from your subject this last one is the best way to create a prof looking picture here are some pictures taken in dark areas without flash ... i used both auto and background defocus settings hope it is been helpful ...

text_review: and really first ice run of my life we got four inches of snow then an hour of thirty-four degree light rain then an immediate drop to twenty degrees everything froze solid an inch of ice covered every surface around this is in south korea for reference i was excited for my first frozen run with my icebugs bought them two weeks ago because i knew this was coming three miles including a four hundred foot high hill that had a nearly half mile downslope that was frozen and poorly lit at five am ice covering eighty-five of everything the few road intersections where it had been heavily salted made up the rest asphalt and nary a slip was had surefooted even confidence inspiring the only part that was treacherous were the solid ice balls up to four in diameter strewn through my poorly lit path stepped on a few of those and tweaked my ankles slightly but even with the reactions to those the pytho 2s never so much as skidded and they handled the asphalt with aplomb just the weird sound of the studs clacking they sounded like suckers on glass being removed quickly or bubble wrap being popped either way great buy the only downside was the insoles which seem thin and really kind of weak i pulled out my brooks ghost insoles and put them in instead perfect fit and they are exceptionally comfortable five stars all around love these things oh and they are water resistant have yet to get so much as damp on me and i have run them through slush and puddles too and look pretty cool on top of it love these shoes

text_review: triggerfinger is a power-trio from belgium that has been steadily getting better and bigger over there from their self-titled two thousand and four album and on to two thousand and eight s what grabs ya in two thousand and ten came the band highly-anticipated third studio album if you are not familiar with triggerfinger's sound think heavy guitar-based rock not unlike say the child of a foo fighters queens of the stone age black sabbath merger all this dancin around eleven tracks fifty-one min kick off with the furious title track and we are off to the races let it ride is anotehr short take-no-prisoners song on love lost in love singer-songwriter ruben block starts deviating from the straight-on rock and that is actually good news as we get to hear different sides of the band all night long is an outright slow song with block's vocals heavily distorted the epic feed me closes off the first half of the album nicely the second half of the album starts with a blazing cherry check out in particular the intro there are several longer songs as well including the eight min slow-burner my baby's got a gun and the six min album closer it has not gone away which in and of itself sums up the album nicely.in all this is a very good album i might have left off the weakest song so as to get a slightly shorter and more concise running time but it is a minore quibble by reputation the band really shines in concert they released a live album in two thousand and seven faders up live and are about to release another live album live at high voltage later this fall i have not gotten the opportunity to see them live but i can only hope they will tour the us at some point as an aside triggerfinger is one of a core group of up-and-coming belgian bands worth checking out see in particular also the black box revelantion and customs

text_review: pop trash is probably the best work duran duran has put out to date the blend of melodic lyrics cool rhythms and great synth and guitar work just makes it the must have album of the new millenium ... or any millenium someone else not me is the beautiful ballad with beautiful lyrics and even more beautiful music to back it lava lamp i think is the feel good tune of the album as it makes you just wanna get up and dance playing with uranium is a very cool funky track with a great blend of guitar and synth and i see this as a definate choice for a single hallucinating elvis is probably the funkiest song on the album and it proves a real stong track for the middle of the record starting to remember is a little odd in the beats at times but still a strong track with an interesting ending pop trash movie is a beautiful song and i think it was meant to be a duran song fragment is a beautiful short piece although i wish it went longer mars meets venus and lady xanax are my personal favourites on the album both being songs with great melodies and great lyrics lady xanax has sort of a haunting soung to it as lady ice of so red the rose did kiss goodbye is probably my favourite of the two interludes and again i wish it was a full length song last day on earth is a powerful rocking song to end the album with and i think it should be a possible single as well the bonus someone else not me en espanol was a great treat as i think simon makes it sound great no matter what language he is singing in the cover art and the linear art was great and it makes it fun to look at as well as listen to overall this gets a fifteen out of ten on my scale and goes down as my favourite duran album ... stronger than rio great job duran duran and i hope the next is as good as pop trash

text_review: lost nite records was founded in the early 1960s by jerry greene and jared weinstein after greene who was still in his teens and working for comped vinyl at a nyc record store came across an obscure forty-five by the capris there is a moon out tonight he made it a national hit by first buying the master tape and then inking a distribution deal with old town records greene and weinstein relocated to philadelphia and partnered in lost nite with local dj jerry blavat aka the geator with the heator eventually lost nite became the premier name in obscure and reissued doowop r b and r r singles.the label's compilation lps were not all that carefully mastered forty-five speed surface noise and ticks can sometimes be heard and especially on their twenty-two song albums output levels and frequency range are somewhat limited lost nite's various deejay collections may have spoken comments that overlap songs wfil fifty-six 50th anniversary golden greats ln-lp one hundred and forty-six is a stereo lp from one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-two exceptions tracks by jerry butler and edison lighthouse are rechanneled mono as is the lp version of house of the rising sun the robin ward cut is straight monaural.dick clark started djing at rock roll pioneer wfil five hundred and sixty in one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-two this was philly's highest rated top forty boss radio station in the 60s known to locals as the pop music explosion listeners all had their favorite boss jock be it chuck browning captain jay cook diamond jim nettleton king george michael long john wade or dave the rave parks who manned the overnite shift in later years fil featured dr don rose j j jeffrey tiny tom tyler big ron o'brien and k c hill among others includes release dates plus text_review: i live overseas in a furnished house which means i do not have my own bed with me the bed we were provided is granite-hard i found myself waking up several times during the night with an aching hip or shoulder or worse with one or both of my arms so numb that i had to sit up for several minutes just to get the blood flowing again.this mattress pad was an adequate solution to an inadequate sleeping situation while the bed still is not as soft as i would like it i find that i rarely have any of the problems that i had pre-mattress pad the quality of my sleep has improved dramatically as has the quality of my wife's sleep as she no longer has to deal with me repositioning myself all night an overall worthwhile purchase i would recommend it to anyone dealing with the same issues i was having

text_review: years ago pre hd i had signal issues with cable strength to a couple cable ready analog sets i am 400ft off the road another sixty ft or so from a pedestal to the house i installed a motorola four way amp fixed it all then a storm blew it out comcast eventually buried new cable from pedistal to house.that fixed it all now with adding hd i had issues with some channels on a comcast xfinity hd unit the unit is the furthest 75ft from the systems entry point a two way splitter to a modem four way splitter that goes to two analogs two sony lcd's one on the hd unit the other straight cable to coax input the instructions suggested to install the unit at the entry point of the cable i installed the amp in the room w hd unit the channels that were the usual issues were acting up i installed the amp all was fixed did another a-b test and all good so time will tell if issues return or if installing at end of 75ft cable run before hd unit causes other problems then i will install at entry point either prior to four way or between four way house cable but initial results are good.instructions were thorough but no mention of the grounding screw i have no easily accessable ground in the room i would have one at the entry point

text_review: i have tried many different noise canceling headphones and determined that the quiet comfort three are the best on the market at first these headphones sound like a piece of crap but after you break them in for about a week the sound is gorgeous when i first got these headphones i was stunned at the level of noise reduction to test them out i turned on some music on my home theater system then connected these headphones to a zune hd before the music on the zune even started playing i was amazed at how little i could hear from my home theater system when the music began playing i could not believe my ears i could not hear a sound but the audio quality was not the best and my ears felt like there were being sucked in after about five minutes of use i noticed i yawning quite a lot the next day i went out and bought the beats by dr dre and took them home to test them when i first put them on i noticed hard and striking bass the base in these headphones were actually better then the bose there was also pretty good treble as i started listening to these headphones a little bet more and the results were not to good in some songs the treble and bass were perfect but in other songs there was way to much base i did a little research on the beats and found out that these headphones were made for hip hop as stated by dr dre himself who is the creator of these headphones said that when he herd in the club by fifty cent was when he knew he had created the perfect headphones being an audiophile i was not really wild about this idea so i went back to the bose one thing i did like about the beats was that it has a mute button on the side when i started using the bose again i noticed that they sounded a lot better then they once did i was yawning significantly less my ears were not a sucked in and that the bose were a lot smaller and lighter the the beats so i returned the beats and kept the bose

text_review: i had a wonderful pair of sony earbuds before which were similar to these but unfortunately my cat chewed them completely apart ... those were the best i would owned and i wish i still had them or knew where to find them regardless i had to find a replacement and so invested in the most similar pair of earbuds i could find in the hook style but i tried philips those were god-awful and the left earbud burned out after a short while.so this was my next option once i found it from my past experience and my father's headphones which are sony incredibly ancient and working like a charm i figured i could not go wrong.the cord comes with an extender that is incredibly long i absolutely loved that unfortunately on a road trip no less i had a scare where these earbuds were dying on me too you know where you will need to turn the jack in your ipod in order for the sound to come through properly not good turns out the problem was the extender once i deatched that the earbuds worked fine and have been working fine ever since my issue is that the cord is now unusually short but i suppose that has its benefits and i have learned to live with it.now sound quality i have no idea how to judge earbuds on sound quality so i had to experiment until i found a kind that was decent these are excellent if you try earbuds like these you will never go back to the kind that comes with the ipod i will save you time and tell you now to not bother with earbuds that do not cushion inside your ear unless you absolutely cannot stand that feeling even then i suggest you learn to get used to it because it will change your listening experience for the better the noise cancellation is stellar as well which this style is famous for a little fyi my ipod nano at half the max volume is my standard volume during school it is loud enough that i cannot hear a thing around me but the music but quiet enough that no one else can hear a peep from my music even in complete silence.if you can stand it too do not bother with earbuds that do not have a hook i will never change back to any style other than in-ear hook earbuds unless i can someday afford high quality headphones for at-home listening these never fall out unless i really tug them and even then i would need to tug them sideways.if anything happens to these i am sure it will not be for a while and i will be sticking with sony in this style anyway.music even in complete silence.if you can stand it too do not bother with earbuds that do not have a hook i will never change back to any style other than in-ear hook earbuds unless i can someday afford high quality headphones for at-home listening these never fall out unless i really tug them and even then i would need to tug them sideways.if anything happens to these i am sure it will not be for a while and i will be sticking with sony in this style anyway

text_review: i am not kidding when i say that i have been watching these headphones for a while they have been sitting on my wish list and just recently i decided that i could afford to treat myself a little gift i should not have i just got them today now before i continue to my review i would like to note that when i read other people's reviews i usually discard the opinions of those who have only had a product for a really short amount of time because people usually have not had the product long enough to find the issues that eventually turn up or adequately worked through confusions misunderstandings and hidden tricks i however feel quite strongly that if i do not write this review now while my experience is still fresh i will procrastinate and never get it done.before i open the package i can see that one of the silicone coverings is missing i placed my faith in humanity though and opened the box anyway hoping that it had merely fallen out of its designated slot as i did get them from an amazon warehouse deal nope nada gone fortunately they are not one of the sizes i prefer to wear but this did not leave a fantastic first impression with me i take out the earbuds and admire the look of them they look really nice and i was hoping to get some quality sound from them i was not expecting fantastic sound from them but i was hoping that they would be at least a margin better than decent especially with all of the positive reviews that i have been reading i put them in my ears without connection and i can immediately tell that they do not fit in well this was rather disappointing i have adjusted them multiple times and simply left them in my ears hoping that i would just get used to the feel but they fall out of my ears with even the slightest bump movement or pull i was sitting at the computer listening to youtube music and my left side just falls out so disappointing i even changed the coverings to the smallest sizeand i felt no difference.they are not well noise isolating headphones not unless you decide to blast the music to the point of eardrum damaging and sound leaking i am not an audiophile but i wore them during some sound tests on youtube and i really was not impressed by the quality of sound either maybe this is just because i am used to sony mdr-x five headphones which naturally emphasize the bass but i am not a bass fanatic i want good and clear mid and high tones too.to make matters worse my left side was starting to pop and crackle while i was watching some vlogbrother videos i plugged them in all the way i want my money back discounted price and all so far they are not any better than the cheap 5-10 earbuds that accompany mp3 players which i have worn their only saving grace is that during a 3d sound test they performed quite well it earned them some time for a second chance i am thinking that i will keep them around until tomorrow and see if things do not resolve themselves out i am not a person who easily considers returning products especially if purchased online the hassle is not usually worth it seriously if they do not win me back somehow withing the next twenty-four hrs i am returning them

text_review: every wwi flight sim fan has been eagerly awaiting the release of rise of flight earlier named knights of the sky and watching it is progress over the last several years it was expected to be the next great redbaron replacement but what we got instead is a very lean empty feeling simulator that is going to have to add a lot of content to catch up to rb or some other sims much has been covered in the previous comments and i agree with many of the comments good and bad but i will go ahead and add my own list of what immediately strikes me as good and bad or not available yet the best comment was that this is a wip work in progress so just be aware of what you are getting .. and be aware that there is no refund and no way to sell the game dvd down the road or the seven each add on aircraft if you decide you do not like it or get tired of it the on line requirement for single player or multi player is a copy protection system and unless they change things only one buyer is allowed .. so no resale on ebay etc unless they change their policy my general conclusion is that it is inconsistent in all areas so i will comment on the good and bad in each area that i can think of fantastic lighting effects and animated shadows in the cockpit and on objects along with beautiful reflections on water and other reflective surfaces the flight model fm appears to be the best of any flight sims done so far .. it just feels real and comments by fliers of ultra lights and other small planes generally agree it is the best yet the ai artificial inteligence computer pilots seem to be rather docil when fighting and not that well done or not very evasive when shot at .. too easy to shoot down .. the only thing that makes shooting them down hard is the plane you are flying that has this wonderful feeling of bouncing about with every little air currant makes it very hard to aim the cockpits are fully animated with working controls and full 3d .. they are amazing looking but i would like to see a pilot extensions of arms and legs working the stick and pedals as done in some other sims exterior shots show animated pilots and gunners and they add a lot to the feeling of live people in the planes instead of rigid mannequins as in most other sims however the pilots are too small scaled and have been proven to be too small in some forum discussions not a big deal and some still disagree but just one more thing that i feel needs attention dm damage model is excellent with all sorts of plane damage that looks convincing in almost all situations one of the best i have seen terrain is very impressive from high up but scenery objects and textures disappear to close in distance from the player lower down there are impressive looking trees and buildings etc but the colors of much of it look cartoonish with areas of unending prestine grass rivers way to prestine and clean too brightly colored .. the textures are to simplistic if you circle around a tree it rotates to always face you giveing a rather odd look to it over the trenches there is a wonderfull smokey look but the textures are even worse here with continuous non stop craters and at times obvious repeating texture patterns showing along with odd looking grey outlined trenches that look like zippers and other then the explosions going on everywhere there seems to be an empty feeling below that brings up the big problem of this sim it just feels empty like nothing is going on down below if you wander away from the scripted mission triggered event points you do not see anything going on unlike dynamic campaign wwi sims like redbaron or over flanders fields where there are historical events taking place all around you in real time clouds are really well done but very limited in type or looks there are excellent feelings of fog and rain but there are no seasonal terrains yet no snow no frost no spring terrain that is another thingthat will be added later as one of their add ons for free or sound effects are excellent they just seem real and are impressive there are some very well done training exercises with an animated eddie rickenbacker narrating in a very close to real sounding voice figure modeling is good but stilted and not on a par with even older games like mafia plane graphics are beautifully done with full details and many moving working 3d model parts like shutters etc the games interface is beautifully rendered with 3d hangers but very limited in scope and often confusing not well organized and often hard to use like the requirement to leave the game to make adjustments to game settings stick settings etc there is no musical score to add drama to the feeling of the era and very little historical content except for plane information much of the english is poorly translated from the russian which can look silly at times or be hard to decipher so is rise of flight the next great red baron replacement not by a long shot they are going to need to add a lot to get near to that description is it worth buying now absolutely if you want one incredible wwi plane flying experience but with only a few planes and a few plane skins each and very little else to go with it so far i hope people do buy this game and i hope they continue to improve it but it looks like it will be awhile before it feels fully rounded mean while there is over flanders fields which has not received the recognition it deserves and is not widly known about but those who have found it mostly agree it is indeed the currant replacement for red baron created by a group of former early red baron and rb3d mod makers and wwi historians it got undeserved bad forum comments because of it is reliance on the wwii combat flight simulator three game the early phase one and two problems and the requirement to buy it in phase three the payware version three between heaven and hell still relies on having a cfs three game disk available for install but is a vast improvement over the earlier off versions in almost every way the only thing used from cfs three now is the game engine the data base is completely off and seperate from cfs three and there is nothing left of cfs three that is recognizable it has very good flight model though not as good as rof but it is being improved for version four to come out soon and some are going to be surprised it does not have the lighting and reflections of rof but much better varied full seasons with historical weather and terrain textures that are more varied and believable in most cases it has a huge selection of planes to fly including two seaters and thousands of authentic historically researched plane skins a dynamic historical campaign covering the whole war means there is a full feeling of involvement in this simulator with life going on all around you as you fly rise of flight off v3 between heaven hell and another wwi sim called first eagles are all woth buying and playing each having strong points and each a whole lot of fun to play

text_review: i was looking for a replacement stereo system for my existing pioneer deh-p six thousand , five hundred which was manufactured in two thousand and two i was worried that the audio quality would be worse since that seems to be the way most other consumer electronics are headed.after powering on the stereo i immediately realized i had nothing to worry about this unit sounds even better than my old one.the clarity of high frequencies is about the same the midrange sound when compared to other units i have tested is still lacking a little bit but this unit thankfully has a bass booster adjuster which helps a little bit and speaking of bass this unit has really hard hitting bass on my two three hundred and fifty watt ten s and it sounds much deeper and more accurate than my old pioneer unit.the built in hd radio sounds crystal clear on my four way sony door and rear deck speakers also i had never actually heard hd radio before and i immediately noticed a difference when compared to a normal fm tuner so i am really pleased with that then again i am probably the only person who even listens to fm anymore.the bluetooth works seamlessly and has great sound quality and works every single time i use it since the very first time i connected it which itself only took about thirty seconds.the display is very good as well viewing angles are some of the best i have seen on an lcd screen and it even looks pretty good in direct sunlight.it s very easy to navigate through the menus in my opinion and thw buttons do not feel as cheap as some other units also the system never lags and there are no delays from pressing buttons or scrolling through the different menus and screens.as far as any negative aspects ... i really cannot think of any they would all be personal opinions anyway.so overall if you are looking for a replacement head unit that has excellent crystal clear sound a nice display and easy-to-navigate menus lool no further pioneer is still runningstrong and when this one eventually does die i plan on buying another pioneer i would recommend this stereo to anyone who is looking for the qualities i have listed above.hope this review helps you out

text_review: i absolutely love this tripod mount ... and here is why if you have not done so i would highly recommend googling fstoppers iphone fashion shoot it was basically a shoot done to prove that it is not the camera but the photographer that creates beautiful images that shoot was my inspiration for buying this accessory but in the real world sometimes when doing portrait work pre-shoot prep i do not want to have to take out my camera the thing is heavy shoot download from memory card and then sort through it is much easier to whip out my iphone and snap a couple of shots show them to my assistant or text them to someone i decided i needed a tripod mount.buildthe istabilizer is very well built everything about it feels well made the clamping mechanism is strong and definitely does its job what i like particularly about this mount is that it will fit iphones with cases on something most do not as well as other smartphones this is a plus since not everyone has an iphone obviously resultswhile i use this primarily for stills it works nicely for a few short tutorials i put on youtube having a fluid ball-head tripod makes this thing a blast to use with the iphone and will greatly improve your shots i know that this is quite a big accessory nowadays for street reporters allowing someone to throw a smartphone on a tripod and get hd footage that is good enough for on-the-spot news reports i definitely enjoy using this even if it spend most of its time in my gear bag there are cheaper alternatives but this really is an excellent choice recommended

text_review: have not you wished that your snes controller did not need a wire i sure did after i used the wavebird wireless controller for gamecube ten years later here is the retro-bit superretro wireless controller here is what i think of it the controller functions as if the snes was designed with a wireless capability control pad works great all of the face buttons work great ... but as other reviewers have said the l and r buttons are a little bit too close to the palm it is not the trigger finger using them it is the center knuckle and that can be a problem on pilot wings as that hair-trigger reaction might take some adjustment to master after all it is no longer the tip of your finger that triggers it but your entire finger but that is a minor thing compared to the freedom wireless provides.other reviewers have said that the controller did not come with synchronizing instructions and therefore i looked specifically for those instructions as i did not remember how they said it worked thank god instructions came with mine i synchronized it then ... my battery petered out bad luck but they were old dying batteries anyway laugh my head off i inserted new batteries and of course it functions as it should do you love the snes as much as i do then modernize it with this controller i would suggest a two-pack though i could not afford it but it saves you a bit of money and the hassle of shipping two separate controllers you will love it oh yes might i suggest you get some energizer aaa rechargables that will save you even more money on batteries

text_review: the clash put out a lot of great music in the few years they were together in five short years that the core band was together they released three regular length records a double album and a triple album all of these records are essential listening i am leaving off cut the crap for obvious reasons they were great musicians with a lot of different influences and they were not afraid to show it a lot of punk bands owe a great deal to the trailblazing ways of the mighty clash that being said if you want the most concise collection of clash music this is it clash on broadway can be a bit bloated the essential clash breaks it down to what the casual listener needs and what the rabid fan can do with as a deserted island compilation everything you need is here the first album is a classic and should be in everyone's collection but all the highlights are here white riot white man ... london's burning complete control ... all classic tracks that show the fury of punk circa one thousand , nine hundred and seventy-seven and the power of joe strummer's limited voice and of course the wonderful reggae remake of junior murvin's police and thieves the track that showed other punk bands both past and future that punk need not have constraints that was the clash's mo never pigeonhole yourself it must have been difficult to pick tracks from london calling as well considered one of the greatest rock records of all time every track is amazing just as the debut cd this one should be in everyone's collection i believe the band did a great job in it is choices except for the exclusion of spanish bombs this is my only gripe about the cd i think this is an essential track that was left off one should pick up london calling simply for this oversite only six of sandinista's thirty-six tracks are picked for this compilation however the tracks that have been picked by messers jones guitar vocals and simmonon bass display the diversity of this experimental record magnificent seven shows how the clash had their pulse on the musical trends of the day and delve into rap ivan meets g i joe has drummer topper headon on vocals police on my back is a straight ahead rock song with great siren-like guitars stop the world and somebody got murdered are both slower-tempo songs and the street parade is an overlooked pop gem off the record four tracks from the a-side of combat rock their most commercially successful record closes this collection along with one track this is england the best song from the mostly forgotten last record from a splintered mick jones-less clash cut the crap both hit singles combat rock and should i stay or should i go are here this is by no means a complete representation of the clash's music there are a lot of singles and b-sides most are fantastic that are not included but this is one great compilation pick it up and embrace the magic that was the clash

text_review: i am a veteran of inspiration having bought my first copy from the program's then husband-and-wife creators and one of their dads at a computer trade show long ago i have stuck with the program because it offers a quick way to do mind maps particularly rapid-fire an outliner and presentation creator in one simple very efficient and generally bug-free package over the years the company has focused its attention primarily on the k twelve market it seems a natural fit though i think the company could have achieved some degree of success in the commercial market as well however their marketing wisdom may be right the competition for mind mapping software in the commercial marketplace is fierce and there are a couple of microsoft products in this space as well so inspiration ticks on and delivers a very nice product a reasonable price you can put together a simple graphic linked outline or mind map with less than a minute's instruction if that the program comes with a large library of illustrations and symbols you can switch quickly and easily from the graphical view to a traditional outliner view a feature which i find very useful finally you can create reasonably nifty presentations with inspiration as well though i do not use it for this purpose overall if you like having a simple to use but very flexible tool immediately for visual or traditional outlining inspiration is the little wonder that your schoolkid may know about but you do not it is a great little product.jerry

text_review: we upgraded to enterprise edition thirteen the other night and it went very smoothly we downloaded the new software put it on the server and then did our five workstations not a hitch we used the connection diagnostic tool to open the correct ports in firewalls etc.my comments about the new version i hope intuit is reading this ): one graphics are not nearly as pleasing as the old version yuck to the black background two we have two checking accounts and had it set up to show one account's checks in blue the other in yellow we then order checks in those colors hopefully the color coding keeps us from writing a check on one account with checks from the other the new program puts a little bitty colored border around a cross hatched check pattern a mistake can more easily be made why would you take away such a great little feature three contact fields used to be just one big field so we would put in for instance accounts payable john smith the system is taking this information and putting the first word as the first name etc to give us a record showing first name of accounts middle name payab only allows five characters and last name of john that makes for some screwy invoices four invoices are nicest with the invoice number on the upper right now it is in the middle of the invoice that is harder to use.so kudos to the techies that made the upgrade smooth i know that is a difficult thing to do less happy with the graphics types

text_review: i am a perennial naysayer when it comes to quicken's upgrades yes i agree with everyone who complains about intuit's business model of introducing mandatory upgrades periodically that one is forced to take because older versions become obsoleted but ultimately time marches on and software does need to be upgraded once having accepted the inevitible intuit notified me they would no longer be supporting premier two thousand and seven come april two thousand and ten i sighed a deep sigh and purchased quicken two thousand and ten rental property version for all practical intents and purposes this is quicken premier two thousand and ten with a couple extra bells and whistles so my review is for both products.after installing quicken property manager two thousand and ten i checked every account and report that was critical to me apart from the usual cosmetic gui differences i found nothing amiss the migration of data files went very smoothly and for once there is an aspect of quicken's upgrades worth the hassle now instead of four or five separate quicken files intuit manages to keep everything in one albeit larger file in terms of keeping track of backup files this is a significant improvement.also all settings and functionality remained intact downloading transactions from several brokerage accounts continue to work flawlessly i do not download transactions from banks or credit card companies i tried this once for an existing credit card account and ended up with hundreds of unwanted transactions in the upload if starting with a new credit card or bank account i imagine it would be nice to simply upload the transactions from the financial institution doing so into an existing account proved more hassle than i wanted to deal with so i continue to hand enter the couple dozen credit card transactions a month i deal with having recently acquired a rental property i opted for this version over quicken premier two thousand and ten whether or not the additional functionality of keeping a data base of rental properties is useful to you may depend on how many you have i only have the one and i already set up the transactions in the earlier version i am not sure its even worth my while to investigate this functionality but if you have many investment properties this might be a better way of keeping track of properties tennants income flow mortgage payments and tax related transaction this is the only funtional difference i see between quicken rental property two thousand and ten and quicken premier two thousand and seven i have investment accounts some with transaction going back to one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-two e g a mutual fund that i have been dollar cost averaging into since then so for managing my investment portfolio quicken premier is minimally a necessity on that front my only beefs are that one a graph that used to be available many versions ago is still sadly missing they used to have the ability to chart stock price history and market value on the same graph quite useful to see at a glance how well or poorly you timed the market with your purchases or sales luckily i get close to this functionality in fidelity's active trader charting two investment performance reporting continues to be problematic under certain circumstances performance statistics are annualized so at the beginning of a calendar year you could be looking at some grossly exaggerated performance numbers the same holds true for positions you only held for a short period of time what seems to be missing is a simple report that gives you the actual percentage gain or loss on a specific trade for example let us say you bought one hundred shares of xyz corp at ten per share today and you sold it tomorrow for eleven this is a simple ten actual gain ignoring transaction costs in quicken this is annualized to some phenominally large percentage as if you had earned ten per day for the entire year when analysing individual security performance this can be problematic three exporting to excel has never been a strong suit you can indeed export an account to excel but you cannot subsequently update an existing excel spreadsheet this is a pain it would be nice to develop reports in excel that quicken simply does not provide if you go throught the effort of exporting data to a spreadsheet it would be nice if you did not have to start from scratch every time now if i am simply undereducated in the use of excel then please someone out there direct me to the appropriate feature that would allow me to append a new month's worth of data to an existing spreadsheet via quicken export.now for the biggest improvement in the quicken experience since my last upgrade quicken actually has telephone support staff that call you when you have install or program issues i thought i found a bug in the net worth reporting in two thousand and ten i followed the support links under help and opted to have a quicken tech support person call me on the phone within minutes a very knowledgable support rep called me back and spent about an hour helping me debug the problem this included having me upload quicken premier seven uninstalling quicken two thousand and ten reinstalling the two thousand and seven program to see if the bug predated the two thousand and ten upgrade to make a long story short the problem orininated last year and had nothing to do with quicken two thousand and ten or the upgrade to said program now ultimately i did need to find the single transaction that hosed the report myself i deleted the transaction and reentered it bingo problem solved today i reinstalled quicken rental property two thousand and ten and am getting on with my life still i cannot say enough how stunned i am merely to know that after all these years of non-existant customer support intuit has finally delivered all in all i would say you need not be afraid of upgrading to quicken two thousand and ten none of the horror story events reported elsewhere amazon's reviews of quicken two thousand and ten happened if you check my reviewer history you will see that i have been highly critical of intuit in the past this upgrade has enough in it for me to justify the upgrade.good luckaccount to excel but you cannot subsequently update an existing excel spreadsheet this is a pain it would be nice to develop reports in excel that quicken simply does not provide if you go throught the effort of exporting data to a spreadsheet it would be nice if you did not have to start from scratch every bingo problem solved today i reinstalled quicken rental property two thousand and ten and am getting on with my life still i cannot say enough how stunned i am merely to know that after all these text_review: wow ... where to begin as a musician music lover and music collector i can say without reservation that intimacy ranks with some of the most sincere genuine and extraordinary music i have ever heard i have just listened to the cd for the third time and i am simply overwhelmed by what kem has produced this is music for musicians music for those who really appreciate the craft yet also for those who simply enjoy music for the sake of being entertained i will not go song by song but three of the cuts express to me the musical genius that is kem one is human touch a sultry intoxicating groove with the kind of subtle musicianship trumpet echoing in the background the occasional right-on-time keyboard riff that has come to be kem's hallmark then there is if it is love a spectacular duet with maurrisa rose whose amazing voice meshes so well with kem's that you have to wonder why it took so long i am reminded of luther's ability to find the perfect female voice to compliment his own and finally we get to golden days which brilliantly pairs kem's vocals with jill scott's profound spoken word all over a scintillating latin jazz 6/8 groove the result as kem says grown folks music if you do not buy another cd this year you need to have this one in your collection unlike many other artists who find success in their first one or two albums kem did not succumb to the tendency towards more commercialism in his music no he did not seek to make music that is radio friendly but guess what radio stations are going to play it because well this is just beautiful real music
