ipod dock that comes with the ar30 otherwise this is a completely new unit and functions flawlessly i bought the complete sonata component system ar30 dv30 cd30 and np30 to replace my fifteen year old jvc f3000 compact stereo system a gem of a mini-system which i finally had to retire due to the cd player and tape deck no longer performing reliably i have a relatively short wall and a small entertainment console where my stereo system sits so the small footprint of the sonata components is a necessity for me i love the brushed aluminum silver cases to me this is classier looking than the typical black that most component manufacturers stick with but that is just cosmetic and everyone's taste is different ca also made the sonata system in black made because the sonata components are no longer part of ca's current line in terms of performance i am very happy with the ease of use sound quality and functionality of the ar30 and the other sonata components from a cold start the ar30 is a tad slow -8.4 seconds from clicking the remote on to ready-to-play--but not enough to complain about with 40w per channel at eight ohms it is more than enough to drive my klipsch rb sixty-one ii speakers the volume control maxes out at a setting of thirty-nine and i have never had it over twenty-five so unless you like busting your eardrums you will be fine.each component in the sonata system comes with its own remote and they are all interoperable there are dedicated buttons at the base of the remote for selecting which component to control the dvd remote has the biggest array of buttons and is a little heavier than the receiver or cd remotes all the components have simple clear arrays of buttons on their front panels the receiver controls are basic--there's no graphic equalizer for example just bass treble and balance--but i have not found this to be a drawback since the sound quality is crystal pure the receiver has a separate in out for a subwoofer the input comes from the dvd player and works fine with my polk ps10.the sonata line has been discontinued by ca and has not been replaced by a similar small footprint model the sonata is only 270mm wide whereas the ca topaz and azur current lines are full-sized at 430mm wide so if you are in the market for a compact component system grab one of these now before current retail inventories disappear i bought three of the four components from amazon two new one barely used and i got the np30 used six mos old on ebay with careful shopping i paid just 1,008 for everything shipping included if money is no object in your pursuit of perfect audio then you can indulge in higher-end components than the sonata but if you are on a budget or if you need a second system for a rec room etc the sonata delivers terrific sound at a great price

text_review: leaving aside a blatant error in the sub-title roaring 20s yes but the 30s were the depression era this is a fascinating and fantastic collection many of these songs have stood the test of time well.as with all music this old it cannot be technically perfect some tracks have crackles and hiss but this is often how these records sounded to listeners back then when recorded music was a novelty people tolerated the imperfections if you must have perfect sound quality do not buy music this old.there are more recent covers of many of these songs and the compilers have included some here which emphasize the limitations of the original ancient recordings i like the puppini sisters and the temperance seven but while these 20s 30s revivalists have made some excellent music i have mixed feelings about their inclusion here still if their presence means more people discover the original music here that is a good thing.there are other less obvious llater covers too including the ella louis cover of dream a little dream of me which they recorded in one thousand , nine hundred and fifty this song dates from the thirties but was revived in the sixties first by the shirelles and later by mama cass.despite some songs being later covers most of the recordings are genuine recordings from the 20s and 30s which capture the spirit of the music superbly i am glad that helen kane's version of i wanna be loved by you was included despite the crackling i like marilyn monroe's cover but helen's presence here reminds me to look for some of her own music hoping that some of it has survived with fewer crackles.whether you are just getting curious about this type of music or you have some already as i do this is an excellent compilation

text_review: after doing extensive research i too came across the viper five thousand , nine hundred and one just like many of you are looking to do now a couple pointers best buy is prob one of the only places that will install a product like this most smaller establishments do not want to mess with something and be liable for something you did not buy from them buying this online is the best way to go but be forewarned first my particular product from sigmaenterprieses came intact but upon installation was discovered either the remotes or alarm module was non functioning this one troubleshooted by swapping the module with one from the shelf the installer noted that there should be a quality control white sticker that covers the opening of the box if yours does not we weary second if you have a newer car say circa two thousand and seven and on then be on the look out for added component costs i had to consider a flcan module that does not come included in this package and is set for a range of models of cars oh and btw all the name brand companies of alarms and modules are all produced by mainly one company directed electronics the module allows the alarm to talk with your car's computer that controls all functionality of door locks windows basically anything electronic third key chip the newer cars including this guy's two thousand and eleven subaru have encoded keys since the idea of auto start is to trick the car's computer into believing a key's in there its much more difficult with these types more than likely you will have to purchase a 556uw this module allows you to place a key in it and wrap it with some type of wire that is able to read the chip inside your key which in turn sends a signal to the flcan just the installation alone with these parts can cost you upwards of four hundred i am in the middle of having the non-functioning components replaced either through sigma or some other way and will post a further of the product when this mission is accomplished

text_review: do you need a basic but docx xlsx pptx capable version of real microsoft office openoffice not doing a good enough job for what you need are you put off by office two thousand and thirteen which does not offer three product keys for your trouble are you even more put off with microsoft turning office into software as a service with office three hundred and sixty-five well you are going to have to accept some compromises namely the hated ribbon and not having all the office apps but there are z number of people who have late windows xp early windows vista era pcs that are perfect for secondary production running windows seven from a retail upgrade disk-and when you do the clean install upgrade for windows which you will eventually have to do due to windows rot you are going to need office and you may never get up the budget to where you want to invest in office two thousand and ten or later for such a low-end often barely aero-capable pc so this is perfect as long as you temper your expectations.with properly set expectations and a legal copy of office two thousand and seven home and student you can now get down to how it works.it works by running basic word excel powerpoint and onenote tasks it is not going to wow you like a new version of office but a common thread i have read in hundreds of reviews for various versions and editions of office is why do they break what works in the previous version when they release a new version well by buying an older version there are no surprises as regards what office can and cannot do because it is been around for however many years it is been since the date the version in question office two thousand and seven home and student which is seven years as of when i write this was made.what can it actually do well word's fully featured as long as you are using it for home or student use excel is fully featured as regards the base program again the same caveat applies powerpoint will get your presentations done although you will miss some of the customizations of later versions onenote is fully featured and it along with powerpoint have the caveat that they are for home or student use the only thing that really lacks in home and student versus let us say ultimate which i use for troubleshooting through over-engineering is the microsoft office tools-you cannot expect fancy things like business contact manager and the accompanying copy of sql server two thousand and five express.in case you are wondering i am reviewing this for my aunt and uncle who sat there and bought a pc in may of two thousand and nine and thanks to a certain ability i have to troubleshoot combined with them buying retail windows seven home premium upgrade through the best buy fulfillment of the windows seven upgrade option that was current at the time along with retail office two thousand and seven home and student that they beat out of hp's customer dis service-albeit with having to pay for it i get to and thoroughly enjoy troubleshooting their pc whenever it is having an issue because i am on a mission to keep them off of the crack windows that is windows 8/ rt /8 one rt 8.1 windows phone 8x windows phone 8.1 x and i thoroughly enjoy every time i can fix their pc that uses this software.office two thousand and seven home and student was a change for them at first from the wordperfect office suite they were using on their old xp computer a dell dimension two thousand , four hundred they replaced it with an amd athlon sixty-four x2 seven thousand , seven hundred and fifty 4gb ram 500gb hd hp pavilion slimline s5120y but then again so was vista and then seven they did not have too much trouble with vista but windows seven home premium combined with this version of office makes them able to do everything they would ever want to do with office and a pc when that changes they will upgrade-and so far it is not changing i just think that office two thousand and seven whether lowly home and student or mighty ultimate or something in between like professional did not deserve the reputation it got as regards the ribbon people were and some still are so angry about the ribbon that they do not like office because of the ribbon i know i am not as qualified as some people to speak due to my aversion to command line interfaces whether of the old school dos unix variety or whether of the newfangled windows powershell variety but i know this for a fact once i properly configured their pc with windows seven home premium retail upgrade on a clean install and reimported their programs files and settings they were using it productively as could be until a virus hit that forced them to pay someone way too much to repair their computer i was able to set it right and from the moment i first showed them how to do basic things like bold underline italics margins indentation in other words showed them where microsoft office two thousand and seven home and student put the tools they were using in wordperfect office they have been happily using office with the ribbon i hate to discount those who have had negative experiences with office two thousand and seven because i do not like most change-especially not the licensing restrictions growing ever tighter since two thousand but i have not had any problems with the ribbon either.so with the ribbon discounted for us and our family we can now move on to infinitely more pressing matters which is how does office specifically two thousand and seven home and student perform in real world tasks well it does not make you have to renew the usage rights to it every year it supports the docx xlsx pptx trio and it has a user interface that aside from being different is actually usable if you can figure out what each button on each section of the ribbon is for which tooltips really help with that and they are on by default in summation for the reasons outlined above microsoft office two thousand and seven home and student is worth the money if you can get a legal copy i recommend it as long as it is needs match up well with what you need out of specifically microsoft office take this as you will two families experiences with office two thousand and seven one ultimate one home and student which is positive and we continue to use office two thousand and seven to this day

text_review: a suitable replacement to traditional analog cameras at decent price point we purchased four of these as a replacement to our analog four hundred and eighty line setup and it exceeded our expectations we only had to run one line ethernet all the way back to our poe switch no more running bulk cctv cables at one hundred and fifty apiece it cannot be beat you can pay two hundred or three hundred for a better camera but its plenty good for indoor use outdoor wise its a little bit sketchy and we do not recommend it if you use it for night time day time its fine see attached another problem is that this will not fit in the outdoor camera case leaving this exposed to the elements and possible shorter life the onboard ir leds when there is dust flying around will make it look like there is a blizzard due to the ir reflecting off the light into the camera if you have motion detect for night time forget it .. it wont work what we do is turn off the ir rely on building street lights and use it for motion detect hardware we have a geovision card software powering a eight analog camera setup two vivotek outdoor 2mp camera and now four of these geovision 1.3 mp cameras i believe that in the near future the eight analog camera setups can be completely eliminated however as we have six ip cameras we are getting close to maxing out our computer network capabilities contrary to the geovision analog card where most data is processed by the geovision hardware network traffic comes thru the computer cpu so i dont see how we can go above 8-10 without reaching the limit of what the computer can handle other thoughts if you have a fair amount of bandwidth and only getting a couple of cameras you may want to consider using nest dropcam with its cloud recording feature and user interface its a world better in the fact that you can access your videos from afar with geovision you are constrained to its clunky interface and lack of cloud features

text_review: my jagged path to ubuntu ... i am not a professional developer nor am i that linux savvy before this distribution i have only had some minor linux experience trying to install off floppy disks which the build could not read my modem so i trashed that idea and went back to windows.flash forward a dozen years my heap of a desktop that was almost as old as my daughter took a dump on me since this was my only means of computing at the time i formatted and reinstalled xp off the disk i had for years i came to realize that it did not have any of the drivers for my ethernet card and i could not get online rather than steal someone else's laptop to burn drivers i figured i would give linux one more shot since it has gotten better over the years i ordered this set with my phone since the price was fair.like the low rated review i thought this was a four dvd install but i am not that disappointed that it is not what you really get is a thirty-two bit dvd sixty-four bit dvd a intro to linux dvd and a library dvd obviously i do not need both install disks but i may use the sixty-four bit on my laptop we just got.my ubuntu review i am currently running it on an old dell with five hundred and twelve mb ram connected to a forty-seven vizio internet tv for a monitor yeah i do weird things like this i wanted a pc to net around with and stream content on my tv the install went very smoothly and ubuntu actually found everything on my computer with no issues mint linux could not find my sound card the programs i use for general stuff were already installed or they could be found on the file network and installed easily enough so everything made the transition easier to linux i am still getting used to the feel but overall it is not a bad alternative i looked through some other distros of linux and found some kde builds that are more like windows but they require ram i do not have in the end ubuntu offered the best environment to use given my resources.if you are new to linux and want to jump in this is a good start i had it up and running in no time and can do just about anything i did with windows visually it is not as pretty as the kde builds like fedora and the feel is like windows 3.1 but it is growing on me.if you are wanting to try different distros you can download them and burn the iso to disk yourself and save money anyone with an average idea on computers can do this.download iso fileburn image to diskboot from cd dvd to install many have a try it feature i would suggest playing around on an old pc first so you do not mess up data and keep you are real one handy just in case you need to reburn or look at info.hope this helps.don t be afraid of change look around and familiarize yourself then step right in

text_review: i love packing cubes for casual t-shirts and shorts however the cubes wrinkle dressy shirts and pants too much so this is a good alternative to packing cubes for your dressier items you just use the included folding board to fold your shirts and pants into the same size stack them one on top of another and close the four flaps which are kept shut by velcro since these tight flaps prevent any shifting in transit all of my shirts and pants stay relatively wrinkle-free this folder also compacts the clothes to make more room for your other items i has always been a pain to pack unpack repack for a trip now i just pack once put the folders cubes into the hotel dresser and take out what i need on the night before my departure i just put back the clothes that i had used without needing to repack the entire suitcase this folder along with my packing cubes just makes packing so much easier no more packing into cavernous bags unpacking wrinkled clothes which had shifted in transit and repacking everything the night before my departure i highly recommend this product

text_review: went to best buy to buy a new wiimote yesterday and saw this game i bought both came back and install it on my dell dimension nine thousand , two hundred which is about as pre-built as you can get right no vista driver problems for me right wrong two two giraffes wrong first i had to tell my antivirus and spyware software about a billion times to let secure-rom install second i installed it and rebooted third my dvd drive no longer works i am not sure what changed between bioshock and this game cause i bought bioshock and had no problem with secure-rom back then i bought bioshock full price and do not regret a single cent because i actually got to play bioshock i finished bioshock without even cracking it although i eventually did for a second play-through cause who wants to find the dvd everytime right review updated funny thing i never did install dead space again on my system i just cannot risk having securerom on it again since i actually do tons of work on it so here is a review of a cracked version of the game as opposed to the boxed copy which now sits next to other games i do not play anymore poor hl2 i think ea should have an option when you insert the disk that lets you chose between installing their drm version or downloading a cracked one i am joking but i totally am not the game runs nicely on my dell dimension nine thousand , two hundred which ran bioshock and cod four on high just fine if you compare it to pc exclusive titles you can tell the textures in this game is low quality nevertheless it has a nice polished look the controls are fine i tried it with my xbox three hundred and sixty control but just cannot bring myself to play any kind of fps without keyboard mouse the game forces the mouse turn rate so your character cannot magically turn one hundred and eighty degrees in half a second this did not bother me and i actually think it is a nice way to add some realism into the controls the overall experience is effective and addictive if not for the reasonthe developer stated they said it was mostly about psychological fear with help from shadows and music the game is actually mostly about enemies popping out or dropping down from ceilings they said it is about strategic dismemberment it is strategic the first five times by then it is more like habitual dismemberment shoot limbs for maximum damage does not require more iq than boom headshot nevertheless the game just flows very well and lots of little things are put into it to keep you in the game world ninety-nine of the time it is obvious the developers put a lot of thought into the interface and controls it is something new to the genre that future games can learn from so now having played the game i plan on replaying it on easy so i can just wack the enemies to death and then on hard to give myself more of a rush i think it is worth the money however a big part of the reason i think that is cause i played a cracked copy put together by the pirates which installed the game and not secure rom so i am very conflicted about the whole thing i definitely do not want any more secure rom nonsense but at the same time i am happy i bought the game to support more games like this on my pc i guess i will continue to buy games with secure rom if it is good enough like this one or bioshock but i will still be playing the vastly superior pirated copy instead everybody wins i guess at least everybody who is honest enough to buy the game and then smart enough to download a cracked copy too :/

text_review: i give win eight and this upgrade version four stars because though i do not like it . . . yet . . . i am coming to understand slowly why microsoft needed to make this painful transition and to see just how difficult what they are trying to do is i upgraded from a factory installed version of win eight on a new toshiba satellite i7 laptop to win eight pro because i needed the domain network connectivity i would be called a power user but i am not a network administrator nor a systems expert so this is anecdotal information from my own experience only i hope this post helps but proceed with caution on this advise the most important thing i can pass on . . . and which i did not do is to make sure you are connected to the domain you want to access when you start the upgrade process preferably via a hard wired cat five cable i figured i could do the upgrade install at home and connect later bad idea second know what types of computer names are acceptable for the domain you will be connecting too and of course know your network log in info lastly after the upgrade is complete do not stop updating just keep running the windows update utility again and again and yes again until you are sure there is nothing left to get from the windows update site win eight takes getting use to but it is the right direction for microsoft to take they had to make this painful design jump as some point or risk becoming increasingly irrelevant in today's market but like with xp to vista i am already ready for win nine with the hope it will be a another win seven winner

text_review: just got it in today have to admit its exactly what i thought it would be and its cool i had a screen protector for my psp before and it sucked because no matter what you did it always had bubbles in the middle this one warns you about that but i put it on three or four different ways and only had maybe one bubble and it got pressed out just fine the only thing i do not really like about the front screen is that the edges will not press down around the buttons and sides it is not a big deal to me though.the back screen is slightly and i mean slightly smalled than the back screen but i think it protects enough to not worry about it that went on easier than any screen protector i have ever had even my phone basically both screen protectors have three layers a bottom layer you peel off so you can stick it the actual protector then a top layer to help it stay flat and so you do not scratch anything when you are pushing out the bubbles this top layer peels off after you are done as for the cases well the vita case is really nice the outer cloth might get warn fast but the case itself is really hard and inside it fits the vita absolutely perfectly it has to straps plus its snug so the vita will not move at all i do not think the net on the top lets anything in it hit the vita either the games case is the only real cheap thing in the package its just a cheap little plastic case but it holds eight games and two memory cards i just wanted it so i know where my games are at instead of keeping little cards all over the place.overall its worth the price i am glad i got it protects my two hundred and fifty dollar vita well

text_review: as of this writing rome two is well over a year old and the digital download on amazon is being offered for sixty i managed to snatch it for fifteen during a holiday sale and even then i am still disappointed with this game.the good looks very pretty it actually runs well an issue this game had at launch steamworks community.the bad very simplified and boring game mechanics compared to its predecessors and especially compared to other games in the genre predictable and unengaging ai battles though pretty are still very fast you will spend more time in empire management again a concept other games do better limited multiplayer population it takes forever to find a game still prone to performance issues and graphical glitches unsatisfactory dlc experience be prepared to shell out cash for additional repetitive campaigns reskinned official factions and the privilege of portraying blood in a war game.rome two was plagued with issues at launch that is documented this is the revamped emperor edition it optimizes game performance fixes the majority of bugs and provides an additional imperator augustus campaign the latter can basically be viewed as a save point where you can take command of a large and already established roman faction at a later point in history.if you have never played a total war game before and are very interested in the setting do yourself a favor and wait for a sale and do us all a favor and avoid pre-ordering attila for that matter do not expect historical accuracy here history buffs

text_review: all the publicity controversy identity changing and bizarre personalities aside prince is one of the greatest musicians alive today yet when this phrase is uttered people immediately think that i must admire his ambiguous image and his funny dress-code instead of respecting his musical genius even though i have read as many articles and biographies about him i could find still i do not know him so i am not the one to discuss the real reason behind all the fuss he has been putting out since one thousand , nine hundred and ninety-two not that it matters much since to me the name prince stands for one thing music prince writes music he performs and on this department i absolutely love him simply put no one else i have listened to could flirt across so many genres of music and nail them being incredibly diverse yet so uniquely sounding more than often he surprised me with a song which i initially hated and ended up listening to the most while prince is celebrating his emancipation from major record label it has been increasingly difficult for the casual fans by all mean it does not imply we are any less enthusiastic about his music than the so called diehard fans since we either need to join the music club or having to constantly go on internet and track him down about his latest music venture and more than often realizing that he has changed his mind again call me old-fashioned but i still prefer to go to a music store pay for a well-packaged cd open it and put the cd on while i read the insert as easy downloading music on the computer is i much rather collect a genuine article from an artist on the other hand though i strongly disagree with record label alas film studio interfering with the artistic freedom i do believe the one thing they serve as a certain level of quality control while not saying prince's music released under warner bros are necessarily better they do feel more polished and easier to the ears and those are thesongs that game him the status he has today i do not agree that prince is a washed-out has been as many would claim cynically because i believe this is what prince is aiming for to evolve and mature out of the pop-culture domain what i do agree is if prince continue to change his music releasing scheme strategy he will soon lose more of the even most devoted fans.one reviewer said anyone with half a brain can tell one nite alone ... live is a pretentious album consists of studio overdubs i should really start searching around the house for that half a brain however i do think it would be much better if this box set is titled one nite alone tour collection instead of the misleading word live giving people impression that this is a single live performance other than that the songs that played here are stunning mostly jazzy-funk but there are some true gems on disc two where prince hugs the piano himself playing some of his most beloved hits like adore nothing compares two u and do me baby one of the biggest let down is that according to the accompanying booklet there are plenty more rare and great live performances which are sadly missing here live version of power fantastic is available somewhere but songs like bambi and paisley park where we would have gotten a chance to hear the man himself jamming up the guitar are extremely difficult to find with a box this size three more cds would not be redundant.even though most of the materials here are recycled pasted together from many different sessions of the tour and with the issue of overdubs in question i have to say this is one of the most satisfying listening from prince since a long while ago if you are a jazz funk music fan you will enjoy this if you think the man has lost the touch please stop dwelling on the age of sigh o'the times you might just learn to love prince again

text_review: i was a bit skeptical about buying an aftermarket battery grip for my new canon eos rebel t2i 550d in other parts of the world but since using it i have nothing but good things to say about this part i recently took a short vacation to mt rushmore in the black hills of south dakota and had this grip installed for the entire three day trip i took hundreds of photos and a lot of video note also that i am not an old-school photographer that likes to use the viewfinder but rather prefer to use live view screen mode which eats the batteries much more quickly the batteries that came with the grip lasted for the first two days before running low i had another set and was able to keep on shooting i also like the included aa battery tray which gives you the option of powering the camera with six aa batteries which could be a real life saver in a pinch i would rate the feel fit finish and quality of this part to be on par with the camera itself the plastic and grip are nearly identical to the camera the controls function perfectly and make portrait position photos more comfortable than i have ever experienced i have large hands and the comfort factor is the biggest reason that i purchased this to begin with as the normal landscape position is more comfortable as well anyone who has picked up the t2i 550d knows instantly that it is not a heavy camera and actually is a bit on the lightweight side this grip with two batteries actually improves the balance by adding heft and size which can create a much better user experience the only thing i would caution is to consider buying the package with four batteries to allow for change-outs if you do not already have spares that said i highly recommend this product over the one hundred and seventy oem grip from canon which does not include extra batteries and even if you do not have the spare batteries you can get by on aas if you need to update 11/10 two thousand and ten i have now been using this battery grip for about four months and still have nothing but good things to say the rubberized grip has held up well with no noticeable signs of wear the battery life has not seemed to have diminished with time and use there have been some negative comments by other users but i still stand by my original comments update 4/12 two thousand and eleven this part has continued to hold up well the only thing i have noticed is that the printing on the grip by the buttons has worn somewhat as opposed to the printing on the camera itself which has held up with no noticeable wear clearly the manufacturing process at meike is not up to the same level as it is at canon that said i have enjoyed flawless performance from this part and it has not left my camera since i received it the batteries have held up equally well

text_review: this ontario canada based celtic quintet has all the sounds you  d find from across the sea but there is definitely a canadian-tinge to their music yes the pipes and whistles are irish or scottish but there  s a bass backing that says they are canadian-bred four of the eleven tracks on this forty minute cd are instrumentals three of them originals and the other is a set of three traditional reels the band goes all-canadian with the sole a capella track  the four  minute version of stan rogers   barrett  s privateers  the band  s prime vocalist and songwriter  joel guenther sings his award-winning song  something i cannot see  in a voice and style not unlike that of sting this is my favorite vocal track while  from the instrumentals  i  d have to choose the title track which leads off the cd it  s an original by the band  s bagpiper ross griffiths with a tip to the scottish highlandsthere is one new humorous song william macgillavray that sounds like a traditional pub song but i missed some of the humor as the lyrics were lost in the mix i was told this is the band  s third studio album but this is the first i  ve heard of them based on this release i  m sure i  ll look for more i hope you found this review both informative and helpful.steve ramm  anything phonographic

text_review: i preordered this with my om-d em5 kit on amazon the second it was released february seven two thousand and twelve while the om-d is still nowhere to be seen no big deal i guess it is been only seventy-one days of wait after all the mmf three arrived last week and i unpacked it last night.first thing first all 4/3 to m43 adapters are mechanically the same there is no chip no electronics there are only pass-through electrical contacts the long story some mmf history you can skip to the end if you do not feel like reading the whole thing ): the mmf one came first it came at the time when there were almost no m43 lenses available and when a m43 user had to rely on his her 4/3 lens collection it was also the time when olympus was still expecting to be able to solve in a fast way the issue with m43 cameras being slow to focus with 4/3 lenses i am not inventing this af part it is all in the interviews with olympus techs popping up here and there throughout the years they really did not expect it to be that difficult the mmf one was awfully expensive for what it was but at least had this beautiful metal construction which sweetened the pill a bit then came the mmf two this was an adapter first released in a kit with the 4/3 40-150 mm lens it was a great deal as basically one of the items whichever side you look at it ended up being free given that the kit was at a mild one hundred and ninety-nine msrp.the mmf two was even more awfully expensive than the mmf one it weighed half the weight of the mmf one not a bad thing in itself but it had a flimsy plasticky construction to not help things once the mmf two 40-150 mm kit was discontinued that is once the m43 version of the 40-150 mm was released the price of the mmf two alone went to a whopping one hundred and ninety-nine msrp one hundred and fifty street price for what is basically a piece of plastic.to its defense by the time the mmf two was released olympus had already realized that making regular non cdaf optimized lenses focus fast on a m43 camera will not be that easy especially the swd lenses gee by that time they actually had problems with slow af on their main camera lens m43 combos problem which was only solved months down the line with firmware updates.it was by then clear that the 4/3 lenses in use with the m43 cameras will be only the cdaf optimized ones which all weigh close to nothing anyway so it was fine.enter the om-d em5 camera.this one is the hot one in oly's m43 lineup it is the first m43 camera body to be weather sealed to olympus credit they also released the mmf three adapter with it the mmf three is weather sealed and this is where it becomes interesting the weather sealed 4/3 lenses are for the most big and heavy well not all but most of the really interesting ones anyway so one would expect this adapter to have at least the mmf one s metal construction and solid feel.alas it was not to be the mmf three is a flimsy plasticky thing just as flimsy as the mmf two the mmf one construction is nowhere to be found it is basically an mmf two with an o-ring on the male side which is proof that this thing is expected to be used only with the 14-54 mm mk2 the only oly 4/3 lens to be weather sealed and cdaf optimized and which is not very heavy i know i know one should always handle a lens camera combo by its heaviest part meaning you are not supposed to carry your 35-100 mm zuiko with a panasonic gf three on it by the camera body of course not.still a heavy lens can put strain on the adapter when shifting in a bag you can in the heat of the moment shift weight between your arms and have a few seconds when the load goes on the camera body side you can ... stuff happens i would prefer a strong adapter vs a weak one any time i am not saying it will break on the spot i just do not feel secure using this thing with a heavy and expensive lens.the one that still laughs at all this the panasonic dmw-ma one lumix g 4/3 dslr mount adapter this baby is still selling is still a panasonic branded mmf one and still costs one hundred and fourteen the short story all 4/3 to m43 adapters function the same there are no electronics there just electrics the olympus mmf one expensive and the the panasonic dmw-ma one the least expensive of all brand name adapters have solid metal construction the olympus mmf two has flimsy plastic construction the new olympus mmf three is a weather sealed mmf two not a weather sealed mmf one there is a chinese alternative the jjc something which is even less expensive than the the panasonic dmw-ma one and is said to be a copy of the mmf one not of the mmf two the jury is still out as of whether the mmf two is actually flimsy enough to cause concern as with everything olympus it is up to specs and does what it is intended to do it is just that it has that flimsy feel and look update just stumbled on this description on the global olympus website released february eight two thousand and twelve :\ four thirds mount adapter mmf 3this adapter has the same function as the mmf one and mmf two adapters designed for use in mounting a four thirds lens on a micro four thirds camera body the mmf three features the same dust splash-proof construction as the camera when one of the twelve dust splash-proof zuiko digital lenses of the shg super high grade or hg high grade series is mounted on the olympus om-d by means of the mmf three pictures with incomparably high image quality can be manifested even under severe environments.the adapter has a detachable tripod mount so safe operation is possible even when a large-aperture lens is used love the detachable tripod mount part something definitely got lost along the way didn'tit :d enjoy this announcement while it lasts i doubt it will stay there for a long time ...

text_review: after around one month of using this bag extensively i can say that i have found it to be almost exactly what i would have designed for myself i have taken this bag with me on long commercial flights with several connections in the car for short as well as extended trips on four seater prop planes for aerial shoots etc it always also contains my seventeen macintosh laptop as well plus two extra batteries for the laptop i have packed this bag in default mode relatively full with all the gear i would likely need for a trip for both the laptop as well as the d300 the extra one hundred and five mm macro nikkor lens two lens hoods the sb800 flash additional filters batteries etc yes it is of course heavy by my choice of course but the key is that it can and does handle it all well the camera is very readily accessible albeit not with the lens hood which would require my opening the side compartment for access i have the comfort of knowing that i have almost everything on me that i might need for the shoot and the portability of a very sturdy and well built backpack that fits superbly when completely cinched around the shoulders chest and waist the only reason that i gave it four and not five stars is because try as i might i have not found a way to attach even my smallest tripod except for the table top version which is indeed already in the bag to the bag to take with me the cost to step up to the model that accepts the tripod is rather steep whereas it should have been a rather simple addition to a bag of this dimensions to attach a tripod hooking mechanism nevertheless despite this drawback this is the bag that i want with me for ninety-nine of my travels and which has become not only my one camera bag but frankly my one seventeen laptop bag as well now that i can take my laptop and camera equipment with me at all times great job lowepro

text_review: i just got back from a three week trip to st petersburg stockholm copenhagen and paris lots of airports train stations and cobble stone streets i researched for weeks the best luggage to fit the dimension restrictions by the euro and american airlines had the best durability and light weight in order to fill my case for the long haul i chose the teal color to easily stand out and the in-line skate wheel design over the spinner wheels that may not hold up to hazards outside an airport i made the right choice it is the only light suitcase that has total rigid support around all the sides of the case the stand support on the bottom doubles as a handle to lift the handle opens smoothly and worked perfectly the outer pockets are very handy inner mesh can keep dirty clothes separated.the only negatives that are minor and why i did not give five stars the fabric is polyester and will get scuffs i scotchgaurded the fabric and it helped remove the dirt but if you plan to travel al lot then get a ballistic nylon case the fabric is not waterproof the wheel housing is installed with all screws except one rivet so not easily replaced i wish there was a plastic kickplate on the underside instead of a vinyl strip.this case for the money especially the close out price is a bargain i travel a few times a year and expect this set to last for several years by far the best out there for the price

text_review: i bought this game without having any high expectations for it and we have been pleasantly surprised for kids this is good family fare and it is easy enough for even newer gamers to play think play dates here where sometimes the guest-child has not played but wants to try true it will not take six months to get through the whole thing but there is a lot of value i think in having some games that are challenging yet relaxing and fun as well i like the fact that the kids have to think as they go through the screens since there are various puzzles and projects that have to be completed so they can advance you could blow through the game by doing just the minimum required but my kids enjoyed really exploring the areas to make sure they had not missed anything before they completed the level.note the very first level screen is an aerial dogfight where you have to shoot down four enemy planes to advance the controls are flight-simulator-style toggle up on the controller moves the plane down etc and my kids had difficulty mastering the movement required to get the plane flying right so they could shoot down the enemies they were starting to get a little frustrated so they called in a more experienced pilot dad to finish that one screen so they could go on once they moved onto the next screen they were off

text_review: apple needs competition as it stands without any real competition apple will continue to practice their dirty business techniques and hold back features that consumers want need in their products knowing that people will buy them anyway then offer those features next year as new upgrades what am i talking about the camera taking 0.7 megapixel still shots for starters this is absolutely unacceptable for two thousand and ten i know that the ipod's camera is not meant to be a replacement for your digital camera but at 0.7 megapixels it is pretty pointless if you ask me i think they just took the old cameras out of the older ipod nano's and used them the more i think of it the camera upgrades in the new ipod touch are the cameras that should have been introduced last year in the 3rd generation ipod touch there is no reason why apple could not have put in the same five megapixel camera w led flash as they did in the iphone four the only reason they did not to save this feature for next years upgrade oh yeah perhaps because they chose to make the ipod touch 0.07 slimmer than before too because everyone was complaining about how thick the ipod touch was right i am sure if apple would have introduced the new ipod touch 4th generation as being as thick as say the iphone four with the better camera fitting inside nobody would have been complaining that it is too thick second enough of the glossy metal backs apple we are tired of the scratch prone backs it is getting old sure there are tons of cases out there but again if you would have made the new ipod touch follow the design of the new iphone four we would not need to worry about that highly scratch prone backside of course come next years ipod touch update refresh we will see this new design being implemented you will see hear apple say ... we have a brand new design .. completely changing it is looks .. etc next issue why still offer the 8gb 32gb 64gb models that is three straight years now oh yeah because apple does not have any real competition in the ipod market to rival this so they just keep it here until they have to upgrade it to 32gb 64gb 128gb pricing for flash memory of these sizes would not have significantly increase apples costs they could have done it if they wanted to but did not way to think first for your mass amount of consumers apple of course the new ipod touch does have some good new additions that are welcoming thus the reason for two stars not just one upgraded to the new retina display nice touch no complaints there the cheap little front camera for face time again cool nice touch however this is just as beneficial to apple as it is to the consumers apple would love for consumers to use their video chat face time and get more and more people using their products to be able to communicate with their peers think about it iphone four users using face time with ipod touch users and soon the ipad two will have cameras thus face time with those users .. and by then i am sure apple will allow face time to work with their laptops imacs too how perfect for apple .. all of their products will offer face time it is an old strategy but it will work it will sucker users into their little game even though ichat has been around the typical consumer is brainwashed by apples buzzwords and marketing tactics finally and i am almost ashamed to admit this this review is coming from an apple user fan i love apple i love their products but i do not like the little game they play with consumers holding back features now just to introduce them later for their next generations this is dirty business but without any real competition it is what they can afford to do knowing that people will buy their products anyway i for one have held back for years buying an ipod touch first it was because they were not offering enough storage then because there was not a camera now well there is sort of a camera but still it is just not offering all that it should i do not will not buy any product or service that lacks features i want that is the power of being the consumer and trust me i will not cave when i feel that the ipod touch offers all the features i want if i still see value in that product i will buy perhaps next year perhaps but i am sure they will do some similar type of holding back on a feature it would not surprise me time will tell of course if consumers exercised their powers chose not to buy into apple's little game it would force apple to make offer better products for their consumers but that is just asking for way too much from the average consumer they will buy just about anything apple offers and then re-buy it the next year .. and then the next year .. etc sad

text_review: i am a huge nikon fan and already own the d70 which is great however i noticed that during the times when i just wanted to snap a quick picture the d70 definitely was not the camera to do it with while it is a phenomenal camera when it comes to really customizing your pictures i do not know if i have ever had a really great picture come out while using it on auto indoors with the flash on my pictures were all washed out with the flash off everything had a red hue i bought a little point-and-shoot hoping to remedy the problem but it was not much better of course the first time i heard of the d40 it was in a nikon commercial talking about giving them to a town ... i visited the website and thought ha yeah right a couple months passed never really thought about it much .. until the other day when i was in best buy and decided to browse the camera section there was the d40 ready and waiting for me to get my hands on it i took a few practice shots in the store and was amazed that the photos actually looked good no washed out look from the flash or red pictures like i would get from the d70 when it was on auto i spent about five days arguing with myself over whether i should spend the five hundred on a camera i practically already had before i went out and bought it the d40 is tiny compared to the size of my d70 and the weight difference is pretty incredible too while it is not a compact point-and-shoot it is not nearly as hefty as most of the dslr's out there all of the practice shots i have taken around my house have looked fantastic even the shot of the pudding snack pack on my desk ;) the only negative thing i have to say about it is that i was hoping the batteries and memory cards would be interchangeable between the forty and the seventy but they are not the batteries are different and the d40 takes an sd card while the seventy takes a compactflash card other than that i am more than pleased with the nikon d40 if you are looking for an incredible camera that can be used as your everyday point-and-shoot yet still give you that optional control over your photos get this one sure it is a little pricey but it is worth every cent

text_review: wow this icon ntv forty blk bag seems well constructed water resistant padded very durable and high quality i kept thinking that it should have been selling for 21.99 or more not 1.99 see the six photos i uploaded by clicking on the customer images link just below the main picture of the bag starting from the outside of the bag the dimensions are about seven high six wide and five 3/4 deep there is a padded carrying handle on the top plus a detachable shoulder strap there is a web pocket on each side of the bag and a large belt loop on the rear of the bag possibly a monopod or a small tripod could be carried in this loop there is also a small loop on each of the back two corners in the rear view picture that i uploaded you can see a blue carabiner that i inserted into one of the loops the front flap has a small zipper pocket about four 3/4 wide by three 1/4 high i inserted a usb cable into the pocket for the picture the front flap is held down by an adjustable travato side release buckle opening the travato buckle you will see a zippered front pocket that is about four 3/4 high five 1/4 wide and one 1/2 deep the picture i uploaded shows my charging cable in this pocket plus a couple other items within this pocket are two small compartments for carrying items such as memory cards a filter etc unzip the main compartment and you will a divider held in place by velcro that can be moved or removed the main compartment is about six 1/2 high five wide and three 1/2 in depth i put my in there and had a little room to spare note that a couple of the stock photos have a light green hue but it is just the lighting the bag is black and gray overall i am quite impressed with the bag and recommend it with a five star rating

text_review: i have used tax cut in the past and have been satisfied but i read about download install issues with tax cut this year and decided to try turbo tax i found turbo tax to be very rigid for example my wife donates to twenty-five thirty different charities each year with tax cut they just required the name of the charity and amount turbo tax requires an address for every charity if i left the address off tt would not allow that donation to be added now i have the cancelled checks for all these charities but i had to look up every address on the net in order to enter these deductions into turbo another example is that my wife has a sar sep for her business that retirement plan allows a catch-up deduction which the standard sep plan does not allow turbo does not provide a sar sep option and would not allow me to enter a catch-up deduction to the sep calculation tax cut does not support a sar sep either but tax cut gives the option to enter the deduction amount for sar sep that you self-calculate so these are two examples where i had to go through extraordinary efforts to work through turbo's rigidity they seem to think that if turbo does not support it you do not need it at least allow me to add or over-ride at my own risk there were others that i will not go into here i also was disappointed with intuit's itsdeductible web site this site is advertised as a place to enter your charitable deductions for non-cash deductions it provides estimates of donated item's value again it would not allow me to over-ride a value if i knew my item had a higher value i had no option to change it so i figured i could export the data to a spreadsheet and make modifications wrong again there were questions on the site asking how the information could be downloaded but no answers intuit wants to lock up your data so you cannot get away.tax cut also does the job with what seems to be less rigidity i will probably go back to tax cut next year

text_review: bond are four young classically-trained babes based in britain who play violins viola cello but no you cannot quite categorise them as classical because their classical instruments are blended with dance beats and electronica and the lovely bond lasses themselves dress in tight revealing outfits rather than typical classical-concert dresses let us call these girls classical pop electronica then like the bond girls themselves their debut album born is quite a curiosity but it is an intriguing one---a fine exquisite whirlpool of the classics with top forty sensibility and while looking at the four women on the cover inside photographs is entertaining enough bond obviously have no qualms about flaunting their sex appeal god bless em you have to give them credit where credit is due the girls can play victory is the obvious lead-off single a supremely catchy instrumental that gives you a darn good indication of what bond are all about in one shot but the rest of the album is just as fascinating and i find myself thoroughly entranced by the groups expertly honed pop classical confections but being such a curious group in today's music marketplace only time will tell if bond truly have a long future ahead of them or if they are destined to be a one-album wonder but born makes one thing clear the women of bond have great musical talent to match their great looks and they can only get better born is a very impressive debut by a talented up-and-coming group that you should definitely keep an eye on in the next few years

text_review: though the learning curve felt a little steep at first it turned out that it was not so bad and now lightroom two has totally changed our workflow for the better previously my wife and i would keep all our photos in dated folders and simply keep groups of edits in finished folders but this always felt kind of clunky and keeping up with and finding particular sooc or finished images could be confusing especially when creating multiple versions of photos it did not take long to learn how to take advantage of lightroom's organizational tools to better keep track of everything and i particularly love the virtual copy feature that allows you to create and easily manage multiple versions all while taking significantly less space than creating real copies of the files we are still learning all the editing capabilities we have not taken the plunge into photoshop cs yet but we are photoshop elements users most of what we used to do in elements is now easier in lightroom it used to take so long to open every photo in elements and make necessary improvements but now we can easily apply certain changes to large groups quickly or even go through one at a time far more quickly than before and for any of the few changes that must be done in elements which so far has just been healing-brush-type work it is just a couple of clicks away to create a virtual copy and open it in elements i think what is both the most daunting and impressive about lightroom is the flexibility there is a huge number of organizational tools provided and there is no one way to organize your photos and your workflow with them especially when you integrate it with other tools this felt a bit overwhelming at first but as you learn about what is available you can really start to develop and tailor your own workflow to fit your preferences and needs there are a few small drawbacks i have had the application crash a few times and some operations are pretty slow particularlyexporting a large number of edited photos which is the main downside to the nondestructive editing scheme however it is getting about time for a new computer so hopefully a newer faster machine will improve the stability and speed

text_review: notice do not buy this title w o going through the first one it will make this game way more enjoyable and you will understand the beginning you can consider this title as a 14th century gta tons of stuff to do outside of the main story tons of places to explore same engine used in the cut-scenes is used in the game tons of hidden things insane ways to kill enemies and screw around with the pedestrians they also react very well to your actions the peds improvement over the first title are massive though the xbox version actually runs and looks a hair better than the ps3 version it is still very enjoyable and a full fledged ride of fun and beauty against a gorges score which i think is available on cd i will definitely pick it up very memorable melodies epically that villa one it is technically more difficult to make a transfer of a game onto the ps3 platform for some reason this title on the ps3 has a very light blur glow filter throughout the game it gives it a nice wary warm feeling but it seems to be an attempt to hide other visual issues in the game again the xbox transfer does not have this effect i think still like i said it is really fun pop-in galore the major downfall of this game it is not occasionally it is all the time seems to be more so with vegetation it is very bothersome sometimes like when you are flying through the country side on horseback you see chunks of grass weeds bushes pop-in right in front of you then these pop-ins have a second more detailed layer that overlaps these pop-ins and it is just annoying sometimes this was not common on the previous title this is why i gave a rating of four stars many of the ps3 frame-rate issues from the previous title are fixed in this sequel which is evidence the developers are listening i believe though some horizontal screen splitting is still there when you rotate your camera around ezio on a tall building not too annoying though i was hoping this was fixed because it was in the previous title a-lot everything else is hella fun and amazing great story directly related to the previous game italian renaissance for the first time in games is absolutely beautiful and you feel the atmosphere seriously just simply walking around is entertaining partial spolier :: double-blading an enemy in the eyes makes you quiver and also when you smash in a guys balls while he is on the ground made my jaw drop lol end :: anyways buy it now i will pre-order the final assassins creed title when it comes hope they really take their time on it

text_review: i used to play world of warcraft but quit about six months after the cataclysm expansion a friend told me about this game and i was skeptical i really enjoyed knights of the old republic i enrolled in the beta testing weekend after thanksgiving and preordered to get early access it was definitely worth it for world of warcraft players this is the next evolution of the mmorpg it has real storytelling with graphics and actual dialog with npcs they have really done an excellent job of combining story elements and good group activities the classes are well balanced each faction has two force-using classes and two blaster-shooting classes each has an option for dps or tanking healing the best part is that each class gets a companion that follows your character around you can also send them on missions to gather resources so you will not have to spend so much time farming finally there are no cheesy in-jokes to distract you from gameplay i have not reached the end-game yet so i will update this when i get there.for traditional role-players this is a great game on its own plus you can group up when the mood strikes you for extra fun group quests and heroic areas are clearly marked so you do not stumble into elites if you go far off the beaten path then you will find tougher opponents it plays similarly to the knights of the old republic and the mass effect series you will not regret buying this game so far i have not run into too many of the typical mmo nerds that call everybody noob and complain about everything overall the gameplay is really well done bioware has done an exceptional job at making this game visually apealling fun to play and challenging

text_review: i have heard more recordings of the merry widow than i can count and many of them are enjoyable none however has the infectious charm and elegance of this one thousand , nine hundred and sixty-two emi version true the performance could probably have been accommodated on a single cd with very few seconds to spare and yes there are some cuts but what is presented here constitutes something so special so illuminating and so magical that it hardly matters von matacic shapes this cream puff of an operetta with even more verve that otto ackermann did on the previous one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-three emi recording also with schwarzkopf and one can almost feel the fizz of the champagne throughout the entire performance elisabeth schwarzkopf was born to sing the title role and in my humble opinion no other soprano comes within miles of what she accomplishes here her idiomatic dialogue her vocal shadings and her musical instincts are balm to the ear she easily surpasses her previous monophonic emi performance of nine years earlier and that was a great one nicolai gedda also surpasses his earlier work on that legendary one thousand , nine hundred and fifty-three recording offering singing of very great lyricism and beauty eberhart wachter was a very fine baritone and made some wonderful recordings his singing here however seems to me to be a little gruff a little crude and peppered with too much speak singing especially when heard in close proximity to schwarzkopf and gedda still this was is one of the greatest recordings emi ever made truly a worthy entry to the great recordings of the century series and it showcases the artistry of schwarzkopf magnificently this would definitely be one of my desert-island recordings with the announcement this morning that elisabeth schwarzkopf passed away this recording becomes even more legendary it is a beautiful memorial to one of the greatest sopranos of the last century

text_review: i am a veteran of home video editing biz i used several tools before ulead was one of them i bought cyberlink pd delux eight a few weeks ago and made two home dvds of my family vacation dvs with total two hours of playing time from my experience i found there are some very good features with pd compared to ulead it is very intuitive one can almost plug and play without refering users guide there is not one anyway or i did not find one available multiple video audio tracks a lot of cool transfers fancy stuff easy to render and burn dvds the only headache i had was that the software crushes a lot during editing my system is windows vista thirty-two bit 4g ram 1ghz 20g storage space my video card is a little bottle neck with windows 3.4 index rating it is not perfect for video editing of course but no reason for software crush either or at least there should be a waring message telling me that my system is insufficient no such warnings the software just crushes in middle of my project sometimes just after i click on a button it was very frustrating then i did everything i could to free up enough memory and clicking on buttons like stepping in mine field yes you have to click and wait till you see your project name on top changes from xxx.prj to xxx.prj that sign means system is still busy saving or doing data swaping and hint-message under your cursor shows up then you can move you mouse otherwise software will crush right away so you must wait at least two seconds after each click of the mouse the 2nd worst thing is that video footage may get lost and leaves some random black holes in the time line cyberlink tech support said it was because my footages were from ups flash card drive and they do not support that maybe that was it the 3rd worst thing is that cyberlink tech support hotline is not free i did not know that when you have any tech question and want to make a phone call for answer it is like those phone-sex lines youhave to pay for it thirty-eight per month i really do not like it or you can email and get an initial answer and go back and forth from there each eamil answer takes two to three days bottom line is it is a good software and price is reasonable but you got to have to invest a really good desktop pc before you start that can be very expensive

text_review: the teares of the muses the new york university collegium viol consort directed by margaret panofsky with kathleen cantrell and campbell rightmyer sopranos and morwaread farbood organ has just released its cd ein lammlein 17th century german passion music the cd is both very well constructed and very moving in meditations on the death of christ and its significance the viol consort margaret panofsky and caroline marris treble david fenton tenor jeremy brandt-young bass christina brandt-young continuo bass has been in residency at st michael's episcopal church in new york city since two thousand and seven members include both nyu faculty and students and nyu community viol players the central work on the cd ein lammlein geht und tragt die schuld is a lament in five sections on christ's death written by samuel capricornus 1628-1665 for two sopranos viol consort and continuo the opening work o traurigkeit o herzeleid for the same combination is also by capricornus the two pieces were published in one thousand , six hundred and sixty in a volume titled zwey lieder von dem leyden und tode jesu two songs on the suffering and death of jesus the works of capricornus are not well known although according to the article in new grove they are deserving of more study and performance like schutz who praised his work and tunder capricornus often chose to employ the viol consort with his vocal textures he is known to have written theatre music now lost however his gift for expressive detail is evident in the two works presented here the two texts are by different poets the first o traurigkeit was written by friedrich spee von langenfeld 1591-1635 a jesuit priest ein lammlein is by paul gerhardt poet and hymn writer the texts share an exclamatory quality setting off emotional gestures oh great woe oh sweet mouth oh wonder o traurigkeit has a simple structure of eight five-line stanzas with consistent rhyme and meter the opening sinfonia is repeated after the fourth stanza capricornus does not linger over the text after an opening duet each voice has a solo verse delivered almost conversationally in spite of the solemnity of the subject the sorrow of christ's death and the sins of mankind in verse five there is a striking harmonic crunch on the word mourn beklagen ); in verse seven the viol consort is brought in making brief exclamatory exhalations as the body is lowered into the grave with gentle triplets from the singers ein lammlein a longer work has greater variety a basic ten line stanza is established and then disturbed in the first two sections the opening section the longest contains a bit of dramatic action god asks jesus to go forth and bear the sins of his children and christ responds that he is willing to carry the load the second verse o wunderlieb o liebesmacht marvels at christ's sacrifice the two stanzas are shorter the viols again repeat their introductory sinfonia between the two verses and then play in the second verse highlighting the falling gestures of the voices at the pouring forth of the lamb's noble blood the final three sections are a personal response to the sacrifice and love that the crucifixion represents the speaker desires to keep christ as a friend to relinquish the gold of arabia and its spices to be nourished and guided by christ and finally at death to be placed at his side the beautifully bejeweled bride is splendidly bedecked by the full consort of viols these two works each full of interest easily stand by themselves however the cd is enhanced still further with works for viol consort one also with voice by a variety of contemporaneous german composers between each section of the vocal music after the final chord of o traurigkeit the viols enter with a chord of almost identical sonority thus beginning schein's suite no one from banchetto musicale the ensuing instrumental texture viols out from under wraps is further enlivened withornaments on the repeat--trills starting on the note graceful turns and connecting passagi carefully considered and placed are evident throughout the recording and suggestive of a distinctly germanic style after the dialogue between god and jesus the intrad and lamento by david funck provide a brief but likewise dramatic interlude with fast-slow stop-start motion suitably exclamatory the third interlude transcribed from scheidt's organ chorale and variation no five da jesus an dem kreuze stund prepares by its use of chromaticism the fourth interlude tunder's exquisite an wasserflussen babylon the opening phrases of the five viols establish a rich tonal world which the singer enters with another different lament the hanging of the harps on the willow trees the final interlude a small gem from the st matthew passion by johann sebastiani 1622-1683 o welt ich muss dich lassen oh world i must leave you borrows its melody from another famous song of leavetaking innsbruck ich muss dich lassen from the first the singers captivate with expressive open wonderfully blended sound the themes of the recording are complex and interesting and these singers make repeated listening a real pleasure the continuo team is also very fine the bass viol is consistently attentive to the gestures of the music the viol consort functions impressively as a single entity coordinated at repeats and moments of heightened emotion yet each individual voice is clear the liner notes by margaret panofsky are thorough and provide a springboard for further research texts and translations are well laid out and easy to follow although passion music is associated with a specific time of the year the uplifting quality of the music and performance on this cd belongs to a timeless season

text_review: in late one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-two when i was but a mere lad of twenty-five i flew to new york to attend two concerts with herbert von karajan and the berlin philharmonic orchestra at carnegie hall on the last evening a saturday the only piece on the program was a performance of mahler's ninth symphony while i had heard several versions before the concert including karajan's studio recording from one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-one and the walter vpo version from one thousand , nine hundred and thirty-eight nothing could have prepared me for the experience of hearing this work performed live by karajan and the bpo it was the greatest single concert i ever attended of hundreds bar none it was a performance that has had an almost mystical effect on me the passage of time has not diminished my vivid memories of that concert in fact if you want to come close to what it was like listen to the adagio of this one thousand , nine hundred and eighty-two live recording there are many other great ninths but this one is definitely the desert island record

text_review: while some hardcore h2b fans may prefer the these monsters are real seven which is an absolutely beautiful piece of art to be sure this lp was the real monster that the innocent tinny-sounding single only hinted at while not every song is a classic per se it is an extremely powerful album that is a force to be reckoned with the shimmering buzzsaw-thick guitar production is nothing short of jaw-dropping and corin's vocals are just what the doctor ordered as a kid in high school when this arrived into the world it was definately a refuge from all the typical things one deals with and it bravely offered hope creativity and intelligence in this dream nightmare we call life riot grrl was a very real thing and we should not take that for granted now the message was is ultimately a super positive one and of course the music is as exciting today as it was then strangely h2b would eventually release the sub-par directions single following this seemingly taking a step backwards maybe they were old songs written even before the monsters seven .. before corin formed sleater-kinney and conquered the world over again with the help of her wonderful bandmates of course if you are still reading this but do not know if you should buy this cd buy it ps while i read a long time ago kill rock stars was planning on putting out a h2b cd with both singles and a slew of excellent compilation songs b-sides i do not think it is materialized yet so you would be wise to dig deep to find these compilations as well on krs records k records yo yo etc cuz they are friendly and magnificent have fun

text_review: is not there any minus star rating if there was this game definitely deserves it made in the same gameplay as indigo prophecy dialogues puzzles and arcade challenges it is the worst adventure game i have ever played indigo prophecy was amazing this one is the total opposite totally boring having to watch adam walk around the island almost in real time is like watching paint dry you even have time to go to the bathroom brew some coffee or even cook ... walkthrough for this game is a must so you will not have to walk around pointlessly guessing your next move if it did not take that long i would not suggest it but get the walkthrough before you reach for your pills some of the scenes are too dark for you to find items you might interact with or need later in the game some of them are really in the surrealist realm there is no way you would guess that you might need something and end up dragging adam back and forth the arcade-style puzzles are nerve-wracking you are better off playing it on a n old pc where you will not worry about breaking the keyboard or smashing the screen it takes forever for the game to load once you lose the arcade challenges and it takes forever to reach the challenge you last lost.the characters got on my nerves most of the time and the dialogues are in bad english and childish.thank god i borrowed this game from a friend and did not have to pay for it a total waste of money.my advice if you must try it ... borrow it

text_review: i normally wear a size eleven in vans and adidas i ordered the size eleven in the james lace up and they were way too big sent them back for a 10.5 they arrived and were also too big i held out for a while on getting the ten fearing that they would be too small i bit the bullet a few weeks ago and they were snug but i thought i would give them a try and decided to wear them out of the house no turning back after a couple hours in them my feet would go numb so i took them to a shoe repair shop to have them stretched after three days on the stretcher with leather stretching solution they felt a lot better the night i picked them up however they shrank back and are still too small and are too uncomfortable to wear all day also they arrive with a very cheesy grey finish sprayed on them removing it was pretty easy just about fifteen minutes with a towel and some elbow grease i still have my pair of brown twelve harness frye usa boots from high school and love them but i was saddened to see that these frye boots were made in mexico the grey spray notwithstanding the overall quality of materials and craftsmanship is satisfactory to be expected for the i just wish they fit like my other frye boots oh well if you decide to order them make certain that they fit very well before deciding to keep them as attempting to stretch them has proven to be futile also keep
