text_review: purchased this for my nine year old son for his birthday he loves basketball and i loved that it had the scripture on it to remind him to try and be confident i was worried it would not be boyish enough as most reviewers mentioned they bought it for girls i feel it is definitely gender neutral enough for my son i liked that it was simple and not too flashy but still had some color on it and not just play gray like some others the saying is around the ball on the front and stamped on the back the words bill and jill are stamped right at the bottom of the phrase which i do not particularly like i understand the desire to place a company name etc on the necklace but it looks odd like it is part of the scripture the words are slightly puffy and kind of run together on the front around the ball which is unlike the picture and makes it slightly illegible think bubble letters all touching together i do not know if that is normal for the look or if my son's is an exception the chain is quite long my son is on the tall side and the basketball hangs right at his sternum i will be getting a shorter chain for him soon.overall my son likes this necklace and i like it for the price despite not loving that the chain is longer than i want for him and the letters are slightly jumbled i do believe i will buy another one for my son's friend and hope that theirs turns out a little nicer

text_review: at first impression ms office two thousand and seven appears to be much improved unfortunately i have not been able to fully evaluate it because of the time devoted to technical support initially i experienced errors that prevented the calendar and mail to display later it was only the mail and this happened sporatically i use ms hotmail as one of my mail accounts and this account would not appear from time to time and could not be displayed i found it necessary to restart office which sometimes worked and if not i would restart my computer naturally this is very frustrating when one has a lot of work to do then add the time on the phone with support sometimes over an hour and it is intolerable i truly began researching macs out of frustration and may yet be compelled to change os after numerous calls to support including a number of times when support was given free control to solve the problem the best that support could say was we will keep your issue open and i will do some research to find out what is causing the errors bottom line is that it was not resolved my fear has been that there are other issues lurking that i have not discovered and will not have free support when they appear support did say that as long as the current issue was not resolved i would have free support for that issue but what about the other parts of office seven i switched from palm to ms os when i purchased a treo if office seven is continues to be a problem i will be stuck with the phone and software note palm treo is available with palm desktop software as well as ms i am beginning get an appetite for fruit ... maybe an apple

text_review: customer service is highly problematic i couldn  t find a customer service phone number there  s no support website with faqs or searchable knowledge bases only a web form for submitting questions before purchasing i submitted a simple question about the length of the ac cord and possibilities for extension cables my auto-reply email promised a reply within twenty-four hours three days later i submitted another one after which i finally received a totally unhelpful reply which ignored my question about cable length and said  i don  t know  about extension cables by that point i had already ordered the camera the ac cord is actually very long which pleased me but everything else that followed was extremely disappointing to connect to the camera the instructions say to use the id and default password at the back of the camera i tried dozens of time and received authentication errors each time i couldn  t log into the camera finally i tried entering  admin  for both username and password voila luckily i didn  t wait for customer service to respond to my question about this  three days later i still haven  t received a reply.the biggest problem with this camera is its very weak internal antenna there  s no possibility of adding an external antenna the camera needs to be very close to a router or extender to work properly i have the camera closer to a router than one of my computers which uses a usb wi-fi adapter the computer connects beautifully to a router upstairs but the movo camera can  t even connect properly to the extender in the next room the router upstairs is utterly hopeless for the camera judging by the signal strength indicators inside the user interface there shouldn  t be a problem connecting i think the camera  s signal strength indicator bars are totally misleading there  s not enough signal strength to do anything with this camera totally useless video appears as frozen images because nothing moves unless the camera is within fifteen feet of a router or extender.even if i could place the camera where i need to i wouldn  t be able to use the motion detection feature this feature doesn  t even work in the user interface clicking on alarm --> motion detection leads to a dead end access error page not found when trying to obtain en motiondect_other asp cannot open url en motiondect_other asp changing the browser makes no difference.given such an obviously stupid programming error i assumed there would be a firmware fix but the website doesn  t seem to offer any firmware updates and guess what happened when i contacted customer service about this issue nothing of course my experience suggests there is no customer service i  m returning this useless camera

text_review: mariah has had hit after hit over the years but when she finally broke free of sony's restrictive hold on her the first album charmbracelet felt like it was lacking some of the power behind the still great lyrics it left some wondering if maybe she needed the powerhouses behind her but with emancipation of mimi mariah proves she does not need anyone but herself to soar up the charts to number one and stay there sure there are some great collaborations with snoop jd twista nelly on emancipation but the most important thing is that mariah's voice is back on charmbracelet she tried this sultry whisper thing to be softer and a bit more subtle she always has had the incomparable vocal range and that should be exploited here she sings back at the top of her range allowing listeners once again to be amazed in a world where technologically enhanced music and lipsynching has become the norm ahem britney and hillary it is more than refreshing to see mariah still able to compete ... and knock everyone else out of the game the best songs off this album are we belong together the second single for its harmony say somethin the third single for the flow with snoop and fly like a bird for its power and message but in the end they are all excellently done and will have you listening to the cd on repeat it is been in my car ever since it dropped and that is more than two months ago i did not want to like to the floor simply because i do not like nelly but even that one won me over the neptunes produced a great beat that really complements her twista's part in one and only is a bit tedious because he manages to referece rims four times but hey not everyone can be the lyricist mariah is this album really does feel like it sets mariah free she says things on it she never has and never would have before and she tackles it all power ballads gospel dance party tracks and hiphop collaborations

text_review: i have used pcs forever that is until about eight months ago i bought a macbook running tiger and a new laptop pc w vista at the same time i became familiar with the macbook pretty quickly and actually found myself using it over the pc ninety of the time then i upgraded to the latest os of leopard and have been using it since the end of october i have been gradually going back to the pc more and more as leopard is really more complicated than i expected i am considering going back to tiger but i have sunk so much money and time installing the new os in the macbook i think i will just wait until they fix a few of the problems and go back to the pc for a while if you have to choose between vista and tiger ... go with tiger but if it is a choice between vista and leopard ... go with vista until some of the gripes in leopard are fixed imho if you want to know what those gripes are just do a google search on leopard and grab a cup of coffee ... your in for a long read sure there are those mac people who will defend the os but there are fewer than you would expect even mac loyal sites are posting tons of complaints instead of praise to me being familiar with both pc and mac it is obvious that apple is trying to be more like a pc it is a shame because that is why i liked tiger ... it was not microsoft oh well bill gates wins we all lose

text_review: i will say up front that for me this is a high-priced item i am not an audiophile i just want good sound that will fill the room both for tv watching and listening to music after reading reviews i decided to pickup this speaker for use in my finished basement for a few reasons first i have brick walls so running a bunch of speaker wire is not easy and will not look great and second because we do a lot of entertaining in that space and having bluetooth capability makes it easy to play and control music this speaker fits that criteria and i am very pleased with how well it performs.out of the box i was surprised by how solidly built it is i had read the specifications but i have to say i was surprised by the weight it just feels like a quality unit my intent was not to use it as a portable device so it is weight and size does not bother me.from the other comments common concerns with this speaker and probably all single units this size seem to be stereo separation and bass i did not expect amazing stereo separation from a single unit but sitting in front of my tv where this speaker faces i am really impressed at how this nearly does the job of the two bookshelf speakers it replaced which were spaced four apart i have no complaints as far as that is concerned as bass goes i am equally impressed by the lows this puts out very happy about that.for design the thing just looks great i assumed it would look nice but sitting on the shelf it really stands out it goes perfect with our decor and has both a modern and classic feel so i would not hesitate putting it in any room i will take performance first but it is a bonus that it is so attractive to look at.as someone else mentioned the inactivity power off is a bit of a double-edged sword for me truthfully i would like this to happen when i leave the room and forget to power it off and i am glad it does work that way but it would be great if i could auto-activate it back up when using my computer or phone not a huge deal more laziness on my part.overall i am incredibly happy with this unit it is perfect for my need.vate it back up when using my computer or phone not a huge deal more laziness on my part.overall i am incredibly happy with this unit it is perfect for my need

text_review: i received this globe a year ago as a gift for my children they occasionally would take it out and spend time with it but only recently has one of my sons started getting serious about independently studying geography so he asked me to update the globe for him that was when what had become a pleasant household educational device became a nightmare when i first registered i was delighted to see that i would qualify for free updates for a year from the date of registration rather then from purchase date so i plugged in my pen started the software and suddenly like others have reviewed found myself with a useless smart pen the program managed to wipe the pen's memory but refused to download the new information into the pen it gave me a dozen different error messages i tried turning off my firewall uninstalling reinstalling everything turning off my antivirus etc ... nothing worked i was left with a dead pen it just made this horrible faint scratching clicking sound i tried updating it on my husband's pc and after a couple of tries finally got it to finish downloading into the pen ... unfortunately it was the 5-8 yr old info way too young for my kids against my better judgement i tried downloading the age appropriate info thankfully it worked after the update was complete it automatically updated the clock.the globe itself is sturdy attractive and well designed and the kids really enjoy it it does not feel or look cheap we keep it on top of our bookshelf in our living room because it looks nice enough to do so oregon scientific really should deal with the software issue because they have something special here but as it is right now it is something of a trojan horse if the pen does not work you will be left with a nice yet way overpriced globe as it stands while attempting to update it you may or may not break the whole thing you should not be afraid to update something you pay this much for i doubt i will attempt to update it again anytime soon and as long as this remains an issue i would not recommend it to others reading through the reviews here it seems this has been on ongoing problem for almost five years now plenty of time for text_review: my wife and i just bought a wii for christmas and we bought this game after seeing a lot of mixed reviews but were intrigued by the concept as of right now i am about halfway through and have been very pleased the storyline is unique and the game play is entertaining i think the pros well outweigh the cons a lot of the negative reviews have focused on the camera but i have played a lot of 3d games and epic mickey's camera is consistent with other 3d games pros great storyline and unique concept entertaining game play that offers a wide variety of options lots of quests and variations based on your decisions which result in a high replay value the different moral variations mean that you will want to play through the entire game more than once the paint and thinner concept is fun if not entirely original i e super mario sunshine cons camera can be frustrating but no more than would be experienced with any other 3d game aiming the paint and thinner brush can be tricky its also important to remember that even if you aim at something you can see from the camera viewpoint you are shooting from where mickey is standing for example if the camera is positioned high above mickey and you can see where you want to spray that does not mean the paint thinner will actually go where you are aiming because a wall or the ground may be impeding mickey's line of sight i have read some complaints about the dark theme of the game it does have a darker tone than one might expect from disney if you are looking for a cutesy kids game for someone under the age of ten you might want to avoid epic mickey

text_review: i was very disappointed with this game the basic idea you play a detective working alongside lenny briscoe and then an ada working alongside the jack's latest assistant is sound but the gameplay is a complete anathema to the tv show in the tv show the detectives follow up blind alleys in their quest for the truth in the game if you follow a blind alley you must immediately load a saved game or you will run out of time or simply lose.in essence much of the early game comprises searching for physical evidence and questioning witnesses while trying to save time the fact that it takes fifteen minutes to bag a cigarette butt is extremely stupid since it means that to collect the right evidence and yet not run out of time you need to play the game over and over to figure out which evidence you need and then go back and psychically only pick up the right evidence needless to say key evidence is carefully obscured by a bad user interface e g a house full of drawers that do not open and one that does but needs to be opened using a key that is in the victim's wallet but itself hidden by the user interface interviewing suspects is even worse whether or not you should ask a given question is totally arbitrary and if you do not ask the right questions your game is over but you will have to figure that out by yourself e g one of the first puzzles in the game involves piecing together a torn up business card just having the pieces with the address phone number or name of the company is not enough what is more there is a witness nearby and the only question worth asking that witness is would you move your vehicle so you can find the last piece of that card.remember if you make a mistake you need to restore from backup so apparently the only good detective or ada is psychic and knows for example that the mineral water has a usable print on it but the cigarette lighter does not sadly you may be psychic but you cannot get lab reports by phone orfax or look up people's addresses in the telephone directory.even worse if for some reason an interview with a witness ends without letting you ask a crucial question you may not be allowed to re-interview that witness even if you uncover evidence contradicting one of their statements i would probably have equally nasty observations to make about the ada portion of the game but i refuse to play it further.finally some quibbles it is not a 3d game everything is pre-rendered so it is a 2d game with pre-rendered video of 3d figures instead of live actors presumably to save money i actually thought that the broadband online demo was considerable better than the game itself with a much less fiddly interface

text_review: if you are reading the comments on this product i am betting you are already an owner and you have returned here to hopefully bask in some glowing reviews if this is you let me say that i really like you and want to be your friend you clearly have a lot of expendable income and a willingness to part with it in the total absence of reason.if however you are still using generic cat six cable that is widely available for even passive lust for this product probably means you have a fundamental lack of understanding of how packet data standards like usb and ethernet work years of reading how high end analog cables revealed the previously-obscured aural treasures has left you thinking that any cable must have some bearing on sound but you see ethernet is different there are frames preambles error correction stop-bits encoding buffering and lots of other stuff in there this is to say nothing of the fact that it is all carried over four twisted pairs in a five-level pulse amplitude modulation that is light-years removed from your precious digital audio signal it is beyond measurements or double-blind listening tests audible differences are simply not possible and they know this.the five star review reflects my absolute awe of the marketing department at audioquest you guys saw an opportunity and you took it there are many technology companies that should take a note not only did you invent a high-end ethernet cable you created an entire line of them with somehow tiered performance brilliant

mediocre games the ps3 on the other hand gives you a blu-ray player built-in wi-fi 7.1 surround sound support more advanced hdmi support and more past games xbox three hundred and sixty wins xbox three hundred and sixty has better games from two thousand and five to two thousand and seven this is because xbox three hundred and sixty has a one year head start and the ps3 presented early programming difficulties for developers it should be noted too that games released in two thousand and five to two thousand and seven now look old and dated compared to the likes of metal gear solid four killzone two and uncharted two on the ps3 present games two thousand and eight to two thousand and nine ps3 wins multiplatform games look a tiny tiny bit better on xbox three hundred and sixty littlebigplanet future games ps3 wins the ps3 is a more powerful console using higher capacity disks blu-ray while xbox three hundred and sixty is less powerful and uses lower capacity disks last-generation dvd in light of current games and console capabilities the ps3 has a brighter future than xbox three hundred and sixty if you want to play games with the best graphics the best sounds hundred and sixty are more likely to pay higher costs for accessories wi-fi hard-disk drives upgrades batteries for controllers they also have to pay fifty a year just to play online paying for repairs after three years of ownership must also be considered microsoft seems to do everything possible to nickle and dime their customers cost of ownership is something you must consider if you want to buy this bundle for kids so all in all this bundle does nothing to make xbox three hundred and sixty a better choice than the ps3 slim

text_review: i had a couple of older model canon elph's and wanted to upgrade thinking new had to be better this camera just did not live up to expectations or what was promised by canon first and foremost i got a lot of odd looking colors in my shots some looked fine but others looked cartoonish i was using the complete auto mode so it is not like i had the wrong settings picked i mean i would hand the camera to a friend they would look at the screen and say why does she look like a cartoon in this one just not natural and not appealing i also experienced autofocus issues where more shots were blurry than with my previous elph the lack of sharpness was a big issue on most prints just too soft and fuzzy i agree with taking fourteen megapixels and going down to ten to make the photos easier to handle and store but not when it affects picture quality to this degree maybe twelve was a safer number still ten megapixels and you cannot get a nice sharp 4x6 print out of it that just should not be happening as far as video goes i also had a focus issue at times with a moving object my son was running around the backyard catching lightning bugs and i lost the focus a number of times and had to move the camera around to jar it back into clarity all in all i would pass on this one
